(void) { GType parent_type; static GType type; if (type == 0
) { static GTypeInfo info = { sizeof (FMDirectoryViewClass), (
(void*)0), ((void*)0), (GClassInitFunc) fm_directory_view_class_init
, ((void*)0), ((void*)0), sizeof (FMDirectoryView), 0, (GInstanceInitFunc
) fm_directory_view_init, ((void*)0) }; parent_type = ((gtk_scrolled_window_get_type
())); type = g_type_register_static (parent_type, "FMDirectoryView"
, &info, 0); parent_class = g_type_class_ref (parent_type
); } return type; }

486static GList *
487file_and_directory_list_to_files (GList *fad_list)
488{
489 GList *res, *l;
490 FileAndDirectory *fad = NULL((void*)0);
491
492 res = NULL((void*)0);
493 for (l = fad_list; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
494 fad = l->data;
495 res = g_list_prepend (res, caja_file_ref (fad->file));
496 }
497 return g_list_reverse (res);
498}
499
500static GList *
501file_and_directory_list_from_files (CajaDirectory *directory, GList *files)
502{
503 GList *res, *l;
504 FileAndDirectory *fad = NULL((void*)0);
505
506 res = NULL((void*)0);
507 for (l = files; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
508 fad = g_new0 (FileAndDirectory, 1)(FileAndDirectory *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (1
); gsize __s = sizeof (FileAndDirectory); gpointer __p; if (__s
== 1) __p = g_malloc0 (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p (
__n) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L *
2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc0 (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc0_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
509 fad->directory = caja_directory_ref (directory);
510 fad->file = caja_file_ref (l->data);
511 res = g_list_prepend (res, fad);
512 }

514}

536static gboolean
537file_and_directory_equal (gconstpointer v1,
538 gconstpointer v2)
539{
540 const FileAndDirectory *fad1, *fad2;
541 fad1 = v1;
542 fad2 = v2;
543
544 return (fad1->file == fad2->file &&
545 fad1->directory == fad2->directory);
546}

548static guint
549file_and_directory_hash (gconstpointer v)
550{
551 const FileAndDirectory *fad;
552
553 fad = v;
554 return GPOINTER_TO_UINT (fad->file)((guint) (gulong) (fad->file)) ^ GPOINTER_TO_UINT (fad->directory)((guint) (gulong) (fad->directory));
555}

638static gboolean
639fm_directory_view_confirm_multiple (GtkWindow *parent_window,
640 int count,
641 gboolean tabs)
642{
643 GtkDialog *dialog;
644 char *prompt;
645 char *detail;
646 int response;
647
648 if (count <= SILENT_WINDOW_OPEN_LIMIT5) {
649 return TRUE(!(0));
650 }
651
652 prompt = _("Are you sure you want to open all files?")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Are you sure you want to open all files?"
, 5);
653 if (tabs) {
654 detail = g_strdup_printf (ngettext("This will open %'d separate tab.",dcngettext (((void*)0), "This will open %'d separate tab.", "This will open %'d separate tabs."
, count, 5)
655 "This will open %'d separate tabs.", count)dcngettext (((void*)0), "This will open %'d separate tab.", "This will open %'d separate tabs."
, count, 5), count);
656 } else {
657 detail = g_strdup_printf (ngettext("This will open %'d separate window.",dcngettext (((void*)0), "This will open %'d separate window."
, "This will open %'d separate windows.", count, 5)
658 "This will open %'d separate windows.", count)dcngettext (((void*)0), "This will open %'d separate window."
, "This will open %'d separate windows.", count, 5), count);
659 }
660 dialog = eel_show_yes_no_dialog (prompt, detail,
661 "gtk-ok", "process-stop",
662 parent_window);
663 g_free (detail);
664
665 response = gtk_dialog_run (dialog);
666 gtk_widget_destroy (GTK_WIDGET (dialog)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((dialog))))));
667
668 return response == GTK_RESPONSE_YES;
669}

671static gboolean
672selection_contains_one_item_in_menu_callback (FMDirectoryView *view, GList *selection)
673{
674 if (eel_g_list_exactly_one_item (selection)) {
675 return TRUE(!(0));
676 }
677
678 /* If we've requested a menu update that hasn't yet occurred, then
679 * the mismatch here doesn't surprise us, and we won't complain.
680 * Otherwise, we will complain.
681 */
682 if (!view->details->menu_states_untrustworthy) {
683 g_warning ("Expected one selected item, found %'d. No action will be performed.",
684 g_list_length (selection));
685 }
686
687 return FALSE(0);
688}
689
690static gboolean
691selection_not_empty_in_menu_callback (FMDirectoryView *view, GList *selection)
692{
693 if (selection != NULL((void*)0)) {
694 return TRUE(!(0));
695 }
696
697 /* If we've requested a menu update that hasn't yet occurred, then
698 * the mismatch here doesn't surprise us, and we won't complain.
699 * Otherwise, we will complain.
700 */
701 if (!view->details->menu_states_untrustworthy) {
702 g_warning ("Empty selection found when selection was expected. No action will be performed.");
703 }
704
705 return FALSE(0);
706}

708static char *
709get_view_directory (FMDirectoryView *view)
710{
711 char *uri, *path;
712 GFile *f;
713
714 uri = caja_directory_get_uri (view->details->model);
715 if (eel_uri_is_desktop (uri)) {
716 g_free (uri);
717 uri = caja_get_desktop_directory_uri ();
718
719 }
720 f = g_file_new_for_uri (uri);
721 path = g_file_get_path (f);
722 g_object_unref (f);
723 g_free (uri);
724
725 return path;
726}

728void
729fm_directory_view_activate_files (FMDirectoryView *view,
730 GList *files,
731 CajaWindowOpenMode mode,
732 CajaWindowOpenFlags flags,
733 gboolean confirm_multiple)
734{
735 char *path;
736
737 path = get_view_directory (view);
738 caja_mime_activate_files (fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view),
739 view->details->slot,
740 files,
741 path,
742 mode,
743 flags,
744 confirm_multiple);
745
746 g_free (path);
747}

763 flags);
764

766}

804static void

806 gpointer callback_data)
807{
808 FMDirectoryView *view;

937 0);

968
969static void
970trash_or_delete_selected_files (FMDirectoryView *view)
971{
972 /* This might be rapidly called multiple times for the same selection
973 * when using keybindings. So we remember if the current selection
974 * was already removed (but the view doesn't know about it yet).
975 */
976 if (!view->details->selection_was_removed) {
977 GList *selection;
978
979 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection_for_file_transfer (view);
980 trash_or_delete_files (fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view),
981 selection, TRUE(!(0)),
982 view);
983 caja_file_list_free (selection);
984 view->details->selection_was_removed = TRUE(!(0));
985 }
986}
987
988static gboolean
989real_trash (FMDirectoryView *view)
990{
991 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic push clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
;
992 GtkAction *action;
993
994 action = gtk_action_group_get_action (view->details->dir_action_group,
995 FM_ACTION_TRASH"Trash");
996 if (gtk_action_get_sensitive (action) &&
997 gtk_action_get_visible (action)) {
998 trash_or_delete_selected_files (view);
999 return TRUE(!(0));
1000 }
1001 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic pop ;
1002 return FALSE(0);
1003}

1010}
1011
1012static void
1013delete_selected_files (FMDirectoryView *view)
1014{
1015 GList *selection;
1016 GList *node;
1017 GList *locations;
1018
1019 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection_for_file_transfer (view);
1020 if (selection == NULL((void*)0)) {
1021 return;
1022 }
1023
1024 locations = NULL((void*)0);
1025 for (node = selection; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
1026 locations = g_list_prepend (locations,
1027 caja_file_get_location ((CajaFile *) node->data));
1028 }
1029 locations = g_list_reverse (locations);
1030
1031 caja_file_operations_delete (locations, fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view), NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
1032
1033 g_list_free_full (locations, g_object_unref);
1034 caja_file_list_free (selection);
1035}

1042}

1078static void
1079action_duplicate_callback (GtkAction *action,
1080 gpointer callback_data)
1081{
1082 FMDirectoryView *view;
1083 GList *selection;
1084
1085 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (callback_data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((callback_data)))));
1086 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection_for_file_transfer (view);
1087 if (selection_not_empty_in_menu_callback (view, selection)) {
1088 GArray *selected_item_locations;
1089
1090 /* FIXME bugzilla.gnome.org 45061:
1091 * should change things here so that we use a get_icon_locations (view, selection).
1092 * Not a problem in this case but in other places the selection may change by
1093 * the time we go and retrieve the icon positions, relying on the selection
1094 * staying intact to ensure the right sequence and count of positions is fragile.
1095 */
1096 selected_item_locations = fm_directory_view_get_selected_icon_locations (view);
1097 fm_directory_view_duplicate_selection (view, selection, selected_item_locations);
1098 g_array_free (selected_item_locations, TRUE(!(0)));
1099 }
1100
1101 caja_file_list_free (selection);
1102}

1144static void
1145pattern_select_response_cb (GtkWidget *dialog, int response, gpointer user_data)
1146{
1147 FMDirectoryView *view;
1148 CajaDirectory *directory;
1149 GtkWidget *entry;
1150 GList *selection;
1151 GError *error;
1152
1153 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (user_data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((user_data)))));
1154
1155 switch (response) {
1156 case GTK_RESPONSE_OK :
1157 entry = g_object_get_data (G_OBJECT (dialog)((((GObject*) (void *) ((dialog))))), "entry");
1158 directory = fm_directory_view_get_model (view);
1159 selection = caja_directory_match_pattern (directory,
1160 gtk_entry_get_text (GTK_ENTRY (entry)((((GtkEntry*) (void *) ((entry)))))));
1161
1162 if (selection) {
1163 fm_directory_view_set_selection (view, selection);
1164 caja_file_list_free (selection);
1165
1166 fm_directory_view_reveal_selection(view);
1167 }
1168 /* fall through */
1169 case GTK_RESPONSE_NONE :
1170 case GTK_RESPONSE_DELETE_EVENT :
1171 case GTK_RESPONSE_CANCEL :
1172 gtk_widget_destroy (GTK_WIDGET (dialog)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((dialog))))));
1173 break;
1174 case GTK_RESPONSE_HELP :
1175 error = NULL((void*)0);
1176 gtk_show_uri_on_window (GTK_WINDOW (dialog)((((GtkWindow*) (void *) ((dialog))))),
1177 "help:mate-user-guide/caja-select-pattern",
1178 gtk_get_current_event_time (), &error);
1179 if (error) {
1180 eel_show_error_dialog (_("There was an error displaying help.")dcgettext (((void*)0), "There was an error displaying help.",
5), error->message,
1181 GTK_WINDOW (dialog)((((GtkWindow*) (void *) ((dialog))))));
1182 g_error_free (error);
1183 }
1184 break;
1185 default :
1186 g_assert_not_reached ()do { g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c"
, 1186, ((const char*) (__func__)), ((void*)0)); } while (0);
1187 }
1188}

1552static gboolean
1553all_files_in_trash (GList *files)
1554{
1555 GList *node;
1556
1557 /* Result is ambiguous if called on NULL, so disallow. */
1558 g_return_val_if_fail (files != NULL, FALSE)do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_200
; if (files != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_200 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_200
= 0; _g_boolean_var_200; }), 1))) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning
(((gchar*) 0), ((const char*) (__func__)), "files != NULL");
return ((0)); } } while (0);
1559
1560 for (node = files; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
1561 if (!caja_file_is_in_trash (CAJA_FILE (node->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((node->data))))))) {
1562 return FALSE(0);
1563 }
1564 }
1565
1566 return TRUE(!(0));
1567}
1568
1569static gboolean
1570all_selected_items_in_trash (FMDirectoryView *view)
1571{
1572 GList *selection;
1573 gboolean result;
1574
1575 /* If the contents share a parent directory, we need only
1576 * check that parent directory. Otherwise we have to inspect
1577 * each selected item.
1578 */
1579 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection (view);
1580 result = (selection == NULL((void*)0)) ? FALSE(0) : all_files_in_trash (selection);
1581 caja_file_list_free (selection);
1582
1583 return result;
1584}

1586static gboolean
1587we_are_in_vfolder_desktop_dir (FMDirectoryView *view)
1588{
1589 CajaFile *file;
1590 char *mime_type;

= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_201
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_201 = 0; _g_boolean_var_201; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const

(0)); } } while (0);

1595 return FALSE(0);

1600 caja_file_unref (file);

1655static void
1656sort_directories_first_changed_callback (gpointer callback_data)
1657{

1673
1674static void set_up_scripts_directory_global(void)
1675{
1676 if (scripts_directory_uri != NULL((void*)0))
1677 {
1678 return;
1679 }
1680
1681 char* scripts_directory_path;
1682 scripts_directory_path = g_build_filename (g_get_user_config_dir (), "caja", "scripts", NULL((void*)0));
1683
1684 if (g_mkdir_with_parents(scripts_directory_path, 0755) == 0)
1685 {
1686 scripts_directory_uri = g_filename_to_uri(scripts_directory_path, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
1687 scripts_directory_uri_length = strlen(scripts_directory_uri);
1688
1689 /* Support for GNOME Nautilus scripts
1690 */
1691 char* nautilus_scripts_path = g_build_filename(g_get_home_dir(), ".gnome2", "nautilus-scripts", NULL((void*)0));
1692
1693 if (g_file_test(nautilus_scripts_path, G_FILE_TEST_IS_DIR) == TRUE(!(0)))
1694 {
1695 char* nautilus_syslink = g_build_filename(g_get_user_config_dir(), "caja", "scripts", "nautilus", NULL((void*)0));
1696 /* If link already exists, or also any other kind of file/dir with same name, ignore it */
1697 if (g_file_test(nautilus_syslink, G_FILE_TEST_IS_SYMLINK) == FALSE(0) &&
1698 g_file_test(nautilus_syslink, G_FILE_TEST_EXISTS) == FALSE(0) &&
1699 g_file_test(nautilus_syslink, G_FILE_TEST_IS_DIR) == FALSE(0))
1700 {
1701 /* Check if we need to create a link */
1702 GDir* dir = g_dir_open(nautilus_scripts_path, 0, NULL((void*)0));
1703
1704 if (dir)
1705 {
1706 /* If directory contains files, we can create the link */
1707 int count = 0;
1708
1709 while (g_dir_read_name(dir) != NULL((void*)0))
1710 {
1711 count++;
1712 }
1713
1714 if (count > 0)
1715 {
1716 /* Create link to nautilus folder */
1717 int res = symlink (nautilus_scripts_path, nautilus_syslink);
1718 if (res != 0)
1719 g_warning ("Can't create symlink to nautilus scripts folder");
1720 }
1721
1722 g_dir_close(dir);
1723 }
1724 }
1725
1726 g_free(nautilus_syslink);
1727 }
1728
1729 g_free(nautilus_scripts_path);
1730 }
1731
1732 g_free(scripts_directory_path);
1733}

1736scripts_added_or_changed_callback (CajaDirectory *directory,

1765static void
1766add_directory_to_directory_list (FMDirectoryView *view,
1767 CajaDirectory *directory,
1768 GList **directory_list,
1769 GCallback changed_callback)
1770{
1771 CajaFileAttributes attributes;
1772
1773 if (g_list_find (*directory_list, directory) == NULL((void*)0)) {
1774 caja_directory_ref (directory);
1775
1776 attributes =
1777 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTES_FOR_ICON(CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO | CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_LINK_INFO | CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_THUMBNAIL
) |
1778 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO |
1779 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY_ITEM_COUNT;
1780
1781 caja_directory_file_monitor_add (directory, directory_list,
1782 FALSE(0), attributes,
1783 (CajaDirectoryCallback)changed_callback, view);
1784
1785 g_signal_connect_object (directory, "files_added",
1786 G_CALLBACK (changed_callback)((GCallback) (changed_callback)), view, 0);
1787 g_signal_connect_object (directory, "files_changed",
1788 G_CALLBACK (changed_callback)((GCallback) (changed_callback)), view, 0);
1789
1790 *directory_list = g_list_append (*directory_list, directory);
1791 }
1792}

1893static int
1894fm_directory_view_get_selection_count (CajaView *view)
1895{
1896 /* FIXME: This could be faster if we special cased it in subclasses */
1897 GList *files;
1898 int len;
1899
1900 files = fm_directory_view_get_selection (FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (view)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((view))))));
1901 len = g_list_length (files);
1902 caja_file_list_free (files);
1903
1904 return len;
1905}
1906
1907static GList *
1908fm_directory_view_get_selection_locations (CajaView *view)
1909{
1910 GList *files;
1911 GList *locations;
1912 GList *l;
1913 GFile *location = NULL((void*)0);
1914
1915 files = fm_directory_view_get_selection (FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (view)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((view))))));
1916 locations = NULL((void*)0);
1917 for (l = files; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
1918 location = caja_file_get_location (CAJA_FILE (l->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((l->data))))));
1919 locations = g_list_prepend (locations, location);
1920 }
1921 caja_file_list_free (files);
1922
1923 return g_list_reverse (locations);
1924}
1925
1926static GList *
1927file_list_from_location_list (const GList *uri_list)
1928{
1929 GList *file_list;
1930 const GList *node;
1931
1932 file_list = NULL((void*)0);
1933 for (node = uri_list; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
1934 file_list = g_list_prepend
1935 (file_list,
1936 caja_file_get (node->data));
1937 }
1938 return g_list_reverse (file_list);
1939}
1940
1941static void
1942fm_directory_view_set_selection_locations (CajaView *caja_view,
1943 GList *selection_locations)
1944{
1945 FMDirectoryView *view;
1946
1947 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (caja_view)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((caja_view)))));
1948
1949 if (!view->details->loading) {
1950 GList *selection;
1951
1952 /* If we aren't still loading, set the selection right now,
1953 * and reveal the new selection.
1954 */
1955 selection = file_list_from_location_list (selection_locations);
1956 view->details->selection_change_is_due_to_shell = TRUE(!(0));
1957 fm_directory_view_set_selection (view, selection);
1958 view->details->selection_change_is_due_to_shell = FALSE(0);
1959 fm_directory_view_reveal_selection (view);
1960 caja_file_list_free (selection);
1961 } else {
1962 /* If we are still loading, set the list of pending URIs instead.
1963 * done_loading() will eventually select the pending URIs and reveal them.
1964 */
1965 g_list_free_full (view->details->pending_locations_selected, g_object_unref);
1966 view->details->pending_locations_selected =
1967 g_list_copy_deep (selection_locations, (GCopyFunc) g_object_ref, NULL((void*)0));
1968 }
1969}

2482static void
2483fm_directory_view_load_location (CajaView *caja_view,
2484 const char *location)
2485{
2486 CajaDirectory *directory;
2487 FMDirectoryView *directory_view;
2488
2489 directory_view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (caja_view)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((caja_view)))));
2490
2491 if (eel_uri_is_search (location)) {
2492 directory_view->details->allow_moves = FALSE(0);
2493 } else {
2494 directory_view->details->allow_moves = TRUE(!(0));
2495 }
2496
2497 directory = caja_directory_get_by_uri (location);
2498 load_directory (directory_view, directory);
2499 caja_directory_unref (directory);
2500}

2521static void

2524{

2526 return;
2527 }
2528

2530 * is no CajaWindowInfo any more.

2537 }
2538
2539 schedule_update_menus (view);
2540 schedule_update_status (view);
2541 reset_update_interval (view);
2542
2543 locations_selected = view->details->pending_locations_selected;
2544
2545 if (locations_selected != NULL((void*)0) && all_files_seen) {
2546 GList *selection;
2547
2548 view->details->pending_locations_selected = NULL((void*)0);
2549
2550 selection = file_list_from_location_list (locations_selected);
2551
2552 view->details->selection_change_is_due_to_shell = TRUE(!(0));
2553 fm_directory_view_set_selection (view, selection);
2554 view->details->selection_change_is_due_to_shell = FALSE(0);
2555 caja_file_list_free (selection);
2556
2557 if (FM_IS_LIST_VIEW (view)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(view)); GType __t = (fm_list_view_get_type()); gboolean __r;
if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) {
2558 /* HACK: We should be able to directly call reveal_selection here,
2559 * but at this point the GtkTreeView hasn't allocated the new nodes
2560 * yet, and it has a bug in the scroll calculation dealing with this
2561 * special case. It would always make the selection the top row, even
2562 * if no scrolling would be neccessary to reveal it. So we let it
2563 * allocate before revealing.
2564 */
2565 if (view->details->reveal_selection_idle_id != 0) {
2566 g_source_remove (view->details->reveal_selection_idle_id);
2567 }
2568 view->details->reveal_selection_idle_id =
2569 g_idle_add (reveal_selection_idle_callback, view);
2570 } else {
2571 fm_directory_view_reveal_selection (view);
2572 }
2573 }
2574 g_list_free_full (locations_selected, g_object_unref);
2575 fm_directory_view_display_selection_info (view);
2576 }
2577
2578 fm_directory_view_end_loading (view, all_files_seen);
2579
2580 view->details->loading = FALSE(0);
2581}

2616 fm_directory_view_reveal_selection (view);
2617 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (view,g_signal_handlers_disconnect_matched ((view), (GSignalMatchType
) (G_SIGNAL_MATCH_FUNC | G_SIGNAL_MATCH_DATA), 0, 0, ((void*)
0), (((GCallback) (debuting_files_add_file_callback))), (data
))

) (G_SIGNAL_MATCH_FUNC | G_SIGNAL_MATCH_DATA), 0, 0, ((void*)
0), (((GCallback) (debuting_files_add_file_callback))), (data
))
2619 data)g_signal_handlers_disconnect_matched ((view), (GSignalMatchType

2692static gboolean
2693remove_not_really_moved_files (gpointer key,
2694 gpointer value,
2695 gpointer callback_data)
2696{
2697 GList **added_files;
2698 GFile *loc;
2699
2700 loc = key;
2701
2702 if (GPOINTER_TO_INT (value)((gint) (glong) (value))) {
2703 return FALSE(0);
2704 }
2705
2706 added_files = callback_data;
2707 *added_files = g_list_prepend (*added_files,
2708 caja_file_get (loc));
2709 return TRUE(!(0));
2710}
2711
2712/* When this function is invoked, the file operation is over, but all
2713 * the icons may not have been added to the directory view yet, so
2714 * we can't select them yet.
2715 *
2716 * We're passed a hash table of the uri's to look out for, we hook
2717 * up a signal handler to await their arrival.
2718 */
2719static void
2720copy_move_done_callback (GHashTable *debuting_files, gpointer data)
2721{
2722 FMDirectoryView *directory_view;
2723 CopyMoveDoneData *copy_move_done_data;
2724 DebutingFilesData *debuting_files_data;
2725
2726 copy_move_done_data = (CopyMoveDoneData *) data;
2727 directory_view = copy_move_done_data->directory_view;
2728
2729 if (directory_view != NULL((void*)0)) {
2730 g_assert (FM_IS_DIRECTORY_VIEW (directory_view))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_206
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((directory_view)); GType __t = (fm_directory_view_get_type
()); gboolean __r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->
g_class && __inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r =
(!(0)); else __r = g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t);
__r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_206 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_206 =
0; _g_boolean_var_206; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c", 2730, ((const char*) (
__func__)), "FM_IS_DIRECTORY_VIEW (directory_view)"); } while
(0);
2731
2732 debuting_files_data = g_new (DebutingFilesData, 1)(DebutingFilesData *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (
1); gsize __s = sizeof (DebutingFilesData); gpointer __p; if (
__s == 1) __p = g_malloc (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p
(__n) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L
*2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
2733 debuting_files_data->debuting_files = g_hash_table_ref (debuting_files);
2734 debuting_files_data->added_files = eel_g_list_partition
2735 (copy_move_done_data->added_files,
2736 copy_move_done_partition_func,
2737 debuting_files,
2738 &copy_move_done_data->added_files);
2739
2740 /* We're passed the same data used by pre_copy_move_add_file_callback, so disconnecting
2741 * it will free data. We've already siphoned off the added_files we need, and stashed the
2742 * directory_view pointer.
2743 */
2744 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (directory_view,g_signal_handlers_disconnect_matched ((directory_view), (GSignalMatchType
) (G_SIGNAL_MATCH_FUNC | G_SIGNAL_MATCH_DATA), 0, 0, ((void*)
0), (((GCallback) (pre_copy_move_add_file_callback))), (data)
)
2745 G_CALLBACK (pre_copy_move_add_file_callback),g_signal_handlers_disconnect_matched ((directory_view), (GSignalMatchType
) (G_SIGNAL_MATCH_FUNC | G_SIGNAL_MATCH_DATA), 0, 0, ((void*)
0), (((GCallback) (pre_copy_move_add_file_callback))), (data)
)
2746 data)g_signal_handlers_disconnect_matched ((directory_view), (GSignalMatchType
) (G_SIGNAL_MATCH_FUNC | G_SIGNAL_MATCH_DATA), 0, 0, ((void*)
0), (((GCallback) (pre_copy_move_add_file_callback))), (data)
);
2747
2748 /* Any items in the debuting_files hash table that have
2749 * "FALSE" as their value aren't really being copied
2750 * or moved, so we can't wait for an add_file signal
2751 * to come in for those.
2752 */
2753 g_hash_table_foreach_remove (debuting_files,
2754 remove_not_really_moved_files,
2755 &debuting_files_data->added_files);
2756
2757 if (g_hash_table_size (debuting_files) == 0) {
2758 /* on the off-chance that all the icons have already been added */
2759 if (debuting_files_data->added_files != NULL((void*)0)) {
2760 fm_directory_view_set_selection (directory_view,
2761 debuting_files_data->added_files);
2762 fm_directory_view_reveal_selection (directory_view);
2763 }
2764 debuting_files_data_free (debuting_files_data);
2765 } else {
2766 /* We need to run after the default handler adds the folder we want to
2767 * operate on. The ADD_FILE signal is registered as G_SIGNAL_RUN_LAST, so we
2768 * must use connect_after.
2769 */
2770 g_signal_connect_data (directory_view,
2771 "add_file",
2772 G_CALLBACK (debuting_files_add_file_callback)((GCallback) (debuting_files_add_file_callback)),
2773 debuting_files_data,
2774 (GClosureNotify) debuting_files_data_free,
2775 G_CONNECT_AFTER);
2776 }
2777
2778 /* Schedule menu update for undo items */
2779 schedule_update_menus (directory_view);
2780
2781 }
2782
2783 copy_move_done_data_free (copy_move_done_data);
2784}

2801 && EEL_INVOKE_METHOD (FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW_CLASS, view, file_still_belongs, (view, file, directory))((* (((((FMDirectoryViewClass*) (void *) ((((((GObjectClass*)
(((GTypeInstance*) ((view)))->g_class)))))))))->file_still_belongs
)) (view, file, directory));
2802}

2808 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTES_FOR_ICON(CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO | CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_LINK_INFO | CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_THUMBNAIL
));

2810
2811static int
2812compare_files_cover (gconstpointer a, gconstpointer b, gpointer callback_data)
2813{
2814 const FileAndDirectory *fad1, *fad2;
2815 FMDirectoryView *view;
2816
2817 view = callback_data;
2818 fad1 = a; fad2 = b;
2819
2820 if (fad1->directory < fad2->directory) {
2821 return -1;
2822 } else if (fad1->directory > fad2->directory) {
2823 return 1;
2824 } else {
2825 return EEL_INVOKE_METHOD (FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW_CLASS, view, compare_files,((* (((((FMDirectoryViewClass*) (void *) ((((((GObjectClass*)
(((GTypeInstance*) ((view)))->g_class)))))))))->compare_files
)) (view, fad1->file, fad2->file))
2826 (view, fad1->file, fad2->file))((* (((((FMDirectoryViewClass*) (void *) ((((((GObjectClass*)
(((GTypeInstance*) ((view)))->g_class)))))))))->compare_files
)) (view, fad1->file, fad2->file));
2827 }
2828}
2829static void
2830sort_files (FMDirectoryView *view, GList **list)
2831{
2832 *list = g_list_sort_with_data (*list, compare_files_cover, view);
2833
2834}
2835
2836/* Go through all the new added and changed files.
2837 * Put any that are not ready to load in the non_ready_files hash table.
2838 * Add all the rest to the old_added_files and old_changed_files lists.
2839 * Sort the old_*_files lists if anything was added to them.
2840 */
2841static void
2842process_new_files (FMDirectoryView *view)
2843{
2844 GList *new_added_files, *new_changed_files, *old_added_files, *old_changed_files;
2845 GHashTable *non_ready_files;
2846 GList *node, *next;
2847 FileAndDirectory *pending;
2848 gboolean in_non_ready;
2849
2850 new_added_files = view->details->new_added_files;
2851 view->details->new_added_files = NULL((void*)0);
2852 new_changed_files = view->details->new_changed_files;
2853 view->details->new_changed_files = NULL((void*)0);
2854
2855 non_ready_files = view->details->non_ready_files;
2856
2857 old_added_files = view->details->old_added_files;
2858 old_changed_files = view->details->old_changed_files;
2859
2860 /* Newly added files go into the old_added_files list if they're
2861 * ready, and into the hash table if they're not.
2862 */
2863 for (node = new_added_files; node != NULL((void*)0); node = next) {
2864 next = node->next;
2865 pending = (FileAndDirectory *)node->data;
2866 in_non_ready = g_hash_table_lookup (non_ready_files, pending) != NULL((void*)0);
2867 if (fm_directory_view_should_show_file (view, pending->file)) {
2868 if (ready_to_load (pending->file)) {
2869 if (in_non_ready) {
2870 g_hash_table_remove (non_ready_files, pending);
2871 }
2872 new_added_files = g_list_delete_link (new_added_files, node);
2873 old_added_files = g_list_prepend (old_added_files, pending);
2874 } else {
2875 if (!in_non_ready) {
2876 new_added_files = g_list_delete_link (new_added_files, node);
2877 g_hash_table_insert (non_ready_files, pending, pending);
2878 }
2879 }
2880 }
2881 }
2882 file_and_directory_list_free (new_added_files);
2883
2884 /* Newly changed files go into the old_added_files list if they're ready
2885 * and were seen non-ready in the past, into the old_changed_files list
2886 * if they are read and were not seen non-ready in the past, and into
2887 * the hash table if they're not ready.
2888 */
2889 for (node = new_changed_files; node != NULL((void*)0); node = next) {
2890 next = node->next;
2891 pending = (FileAndDirectory *)node->data;
2892 if (!still_should_show_file (view, pending->file, pending->directory) || ready_to_load (pending->file)) {
2893 if (g_hash_table_lookup (non_ready_files, pending) != NULL((void*)0)) {
2894 g_hash_table_remove (non_ready_files, pending);
2895 if (still_should_show_file (view, pending->file, pending->directory)) {
2896 new_changed_files = g_list_delete_link (new_changed_files, node);
2897 old_added_files = g_list_prepend (old_added_files, pending);
2898 }
2899 } else if (fm_directory_view_should_show_file (view, pending->file)) {
2900 new_changed_files = g_list_delete_link (new_changed_files, node);
2901 old_changed_files = g_list_prepend (old_changed_files, pending);
2902 }
2903 }
2904 }
2905 file_and_directory_list_free (new_changed_files);
2906
2907 /* If any files were added to old_added_files, then resort it. */
2908 if (old_added_files != view->details->old_added_files) {
2909 view->details->old_added_files = old_added_files;
2910 sort_files (view, &view->details->old_added_files);
2911 }
2912
2913 /* Resort old_changed_files too, since file attributes
2914 * relevant to sorting could have changed.
2915 */
2916 if (old_changed_files != view->details->old_changed_files) {
2917 view->details->old_changed_files = old_changed_files;
2918 sort_files (view, &view->details->old_changed_files);
2919 }
2920
2921}
2922
2923static void
2924process_old_files (FMDirectoryView *view)
2925{
2926 GList *files_added, *files_changed, *node;
2927 GList *selection, *files;
2928 gboolean send_selection_change;
2929
2930 files_added = view->details->old_added_files;
2931 files_changed = view->details->old_changed_files;
2932
2933 send_selection_change = FALSE(0);
2934
2935 if (files_added != NULL((void*)0) || files_changed != NULL((void*)0)) {
2936 FileAndDirectory *pending = NULL((void*)0);
2937
2938 g_signal_emit (view, signals[BEGIN_FILE_CHANGES], 0);
2939
2940 for (node = files_added; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
2941 pending = node->data;
2942 g_signal_emit (view,
2943 signals[ADD_FILE], 0, pending->file, pending->directory);
2944 }
2945
2946 for (node = files_changed; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
2947 pending = node->data;
2948 g_signal_emit (view,
2949 signals[still_should_show_file (view, pending->file, pending->directory)
2950 ? FILE_CHANGED : REMOVE_FILE], 0,
2951 pending->file, pending->directory);
2952 }
2953
2954 g_signal_emit (view, signals[END_FILE_CHANGES], 0);
2955
2956 if (files_changed != NULL((void*)0)) {
2957 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection (view);
2958 files = file_and_directory_list_to_files (files_changed);
2959 send_selection_change = eel_g_lists_sort_and_check_for_intersection
2960 (&files, &selection);
2961 caja_file_list_free (files);
2962 caja_file_list_free (selection);
2963 }
2964
2965 file_and_directory_list_free (view->details->old_added_files);
2966 view->details->old_added_files = NULL((void*)0);
2967
2968 file_and_directory_list_free (view->details->old_changed_files);
2969 view->details->old_changed_files = NULL((void*)0);
2970 }
2971
2972 if (send_selection_change) {
2973 /* Send a selection change since some file names could
2974 * have changed.
2975 */
2976 fm_directory_view_send_selection_change (view);
2977 }
2978}
2979
2980static void
2981display_pending_files (FMDirectoryView *view)
2982{
2983
2984 /* Don't dispatch any updates while the view is frozen. */
2985 if (view->details->updates_frozen) {
2986 return;
2987 }
2988
2989 process_new_files (view);
2990 process_old_files (view);
2991
2992 if (view->details->model != NULL((void*)0)
2993 && caja_directory_are_all_files_seen (view->details->model)
2994 && g_hash_table_size (view->details->non_ready_files) == 0) {
2995 done_loading (view, TRUE(!(0)));
2996 }
2997}
2998
2999void
3000fm_directory_view_freeze_updates (FMDirectoryView *view)
3001{
3002 view->details->updates_frozen = TRUE(!(0));
3003 view->details->updates_queued = 0;
3004 view->details->needs_reload = FALSE(0);
3005}
3006
3007void
3008fm_directory_view_unfreeze_updates (FMDirectoryView *view)
3009{
3010 view->details->updates_frozen = FALSE(0);
3011
3012 if (view->details->needs_reload) {
3013 view->details->needs_reload = FALSE(0);
3014 if (view->details->model != NULL((void*)0)) {
3015 load_directory (view, view->details->model);
3016 }
3017 } else {
3018 schedule_idle_display_of_pending_files (view);
3019 }
3020}
3021
3022static gboolean
3023display_selection_info_idle_callback (gpointer data)
3024{
3025 FMDirectoryView *view;
3026
3027 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((data)))));
3028
3029 g_object_ref (G_OBJECT (view))((__typeof__ (((((GObject*) (void *) ((view))))))) (g_object_ref
) (((((GObject*) (void *) ((view)))))));
3030
3031 view->details->display_selection_idle_id = 0;
3032 fm_directory_view_display_selection_info (view);
3033 if (view->details->send_selection_change_to_shell) {
3034 fm_directory_view_send_selection_change (view);
3035 }
3036
3037 g_object_unref (G_OBJECT (view)((((GObject*) (void *) ((view))))));
3038
3039 return FALSE(0);
3040}
3041
3042static void
3043remove_update_menus_timeout_callback (FMDirectoryView *view)
3044{
3045 if (view->details->update_menus_timeout_id != 0) {
3046 g_source_remove (view->details->update_menus_timeout_id);
3047 view->details->update_menus_timeout_id = 0;
3048 }
3049}
3050
3051static void
3052update_menus_if_pending (FMDirectoryView *view)
3053{
3054 if (!view->details->menu_states_untrustworthy) {
3055 return;
3056 }
3057
3058 remove_update_menus_timeout_callback (view);
3059 fm_directory_view_update_menus (view);
3060}

3068
3069 g_object_ref (G_OBJECT (view))((__typeof__ (((((GObject*) (void *) ((view))))))) (g_object_ref
) (((((GObject*) (void *) ((view)))))));
3070

3072 fm_directory_view_update_menus (view);

3079static gboolean
3080display_pending_callback (gpointer data)

3082 FMDirectoryView *view;
3083
3084 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((data)))));
3085
3086 g_object_ref (G_OBJECT (view))((__typeof__ (((((GObject*) (void *) ((view))))))) (g_object_ref

3087

3096
3097static void
3098schedule_idle_display_of_pending_files (FMDirectoryView *view)
3099{
3100 /* Get rid of a pending source as it might be a timeout */
3101 unschedule_display_of_pending_files (view);
3102
3103 /* We want higher priority than the idle that handles the relayout
3104 to avoid a resort on each add. But we still want to allow repaints
3105 and other hight prio events while we have pending files to show. */
3106 view->details->display_pending_source_id =
3107 g_idle_add_full (G_PRIORITY_DEFAULT_IDLE200 - 20,
3108 display_pending_callback, view, NULL((void*)0));
3109}
3110
3111static void
3112schedule_timeout_display_of_pending_files (FMDirectoryView *view, guint interval)
3113{
3114 /* No need to schedule an update if there's already one pending. */
3115 if (view->details->display_pending_source_id != 0) {
3116 return;
3117 }
3118
3119 view->details->display_pending_source_id =
3120 g_timeout_add (interval, display_pending_callback, view);
3121}
3122
3123static void
3124unschedule_display_of_pending_files (FMDirectoryView *view)
3125{
3126 /* Get rid of source if it's active. */
3127 if (view->details->display_pending_source_id != 0) {
3128 g_source_remove (view->details->display_pending_source_id);
3129 view->details->display_pending_source_id = 0;
3130 }
3131}
3132
3133static void
3134queue_pending_files (FMDirectoryView *view,
3135 CajaDirectory *directory,
3136 GList *files,
3137 GList **pending_list)
3138{
3139 if (files == NULL((void*)0)) {
3140 return;
3141 }
3142
3143 /* Don't queue any more updates if we need to reload anyway */
3144 if (view->details->needs_reload) {
3145 return;
3146 }
3147
3148 if (view->details->updates_frozen) {
3149 view->details->updates_queued += g_list_length (files);
3150 /* Mark the directory for reload when there are too much queued
3151 * changes to prevent the pending list from growing infinitely.
3152 */
3153 if (view->details->updates_queued > MAX_QUEUED_UPDATES500) {
3154 view->details->needs_reload = TRUE(!(0));
3155 return;
3156 }
3157 }
3158
3159 *pending_list = g_list_concat (file_and_directory_list_from_files (directory, files),
3160 *pending_list);
3161
3162 if (! view->details->loading || caja_directory_are_all_files_seen (directory)) {
3163 schedule_timeout_display_of_pending_files (view, view->details->update_interval);
3164 }
3165}
3166
3167static void
3168remove_changes_timeout_callback (FMDirectoryView *view)
3169{
3170 if (view->details->changes_timeout_id != 0) {
3171 g_source_remove (view->details->changes_timeout_id);
3172 view->details->changes_timeout_id = 0;
3173 }
3174}
3175
3176static void
3177reset_update_interval (FMDirectoryView *view)
3178{
3179 view->details->update_interval = UPDATE_INTERVAL_MIN100;
3180 remove_changes_timeout_callback (view);
3181 /* Reschedule a pending timeout to idle */
3182 if (view->details->display_pending_source_id != 0) {
3183 schedule_idle_display_of_pending_files (view);
3184 }
3185}
3186
3187static gboolean
3188changes_timeout_callback (gpointer data)
3189{
3190 gint64 now;
3191 gint64 time_delta;
3192 gboolean ret;
3193 FMDirectoryView *view;
3194
3195 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((data)))));
3196
3197 g_object_ref (G_OBJECT (view))((__typeof__ (((((GObject*) (void *) ((view))))))) (g_object_ref
) (((((GObject*) (void *) ((view)))))));
3198
3199 now = g_get_monotonic_time();
3200 time_delta = now - view->details->last_queued;
3201
3202 if (time_delta < UPDATE_INTERVAL_RESET1000*1000) {
3203 if (view->details->update_interval < UPDATE_INTERVAL_MAX2000 &&
3204 view->details->loading) {
3205 /* Increase */
3206 view->details->update_interval += UPDATE_INTERVAL_INC250;
3207 }
3208 ret = TRUE(!(0));
3209 } else {
3210 /* Reset */
3211 reset_update_interval (view);
3212 ret = FALSE(0);
3213 }
3214
3215 g_object_unref (G_OBJECT (view)((((GObject*) (void *) ((view))))));
3216
3217 return ret;
3218}
3219
3220static void
3221schedule_changes (FMDirectoryView *view)
3222{
3223 /* Remember when the change was queued */
3224 view->details->last_queued = g_get_monotonic_time();
3225
3226 /* No need to schedule if there are already changes pending or during loading */
3227 if (view->details->changes_timeout_id != 0 ||
3228 view->details->loading) {
3229 return;
3230 }
3231
3232 view->details->changes_timeout_id =
3233 g_timeout_add (UPDATE_INTERVAL_TIMEOUT_INTERVAL250, changes_timeout_callback, view);
3234}

3250static void
3251files_added_callback (CajaDirectory *directory,
3252 GList *files,
3253 gpointer callback_data)
3254{
3255 FMDirectoryView *view;
3256 GtkWindow *window;
3257 char *uri;
3258
3259 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (callback_data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((callback_data)))));
3260
3261 window = fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view);
3262 uri = fm_directory_view_get_uri (view);
3263 caja_debug_log_with_file_list (FALSE(0), CAJA_DEBUG_LOG_DOMAIN_ASYNC"async", files,
3264 "files added in window %p: %s",
3265 window,
3266 uri ? uri : "(no directory)");
3267 g_free (uri);
3268
3269 schedule_changes (view);
3270
3271 queue_pending_files (view, directory, files, &view->details->new_added_files);
3272
3273 /* The number of items could have changed */
3274 schedule_update_status (view);
3275}

3277static void
3278files_changed_callback (CajaDirectory *directory,
3279 GList *files,
3280 gpointer callback_data)
3281{
3282 FMDirectoryView *view;
3283 GtkWindow *window;
3284 char *uri;
3285

3289 uri = fm_directory_view_get_uri (view);

3293 uri ? uri : "(no directory)");
3294 g_free (uri);

3304 * one thing, so we need to update menus when files change.

3308
3309static void
3310done_loading_callback (CajaDirectory *directory,
3311 gpointer callback_data)
3312{
3313 FMDirectoryView *view;
3314
3315 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (callback_data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((callback_data)))));
3316
3317 process_new_files (view);
3318 if (g_hash_table_size (view->details->non_ready_files) == 0) {
3319 /* Unschedule a pending update and schedule a new one with the minimal
3320 * update interval. This gives the view a short chance at gathering the
3321 * (cached) deep counts.
3322 */
3323 unschedule_display_of_pending_files (view);
3324 schedule_timeout_display_of_pending_files (view, UPDATE_INTERVAL_MIN100);
3325 }
3326}

3328static void
3329load_error_callback (CajaDirectory *directory,
3330 GError *error,
3331 gpointer callback_data)
3332{
3333 FMDirectoryView *view;
3334
3335 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (callback_data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((callback_data)))));
3336
3337 /* FIXME: By doing a stop, we discard some pending files. Is
3338 * that OK?
3339 */
3340 fm_directory_view_stop (view);
3341
3342 /* Emit a signal to tell subclasses that a load error has
3343 * occurred, so they can handle it in the UI.
3344 */

3348
3349static void
3350real_load_error (FMDirectoryView *view, GError *error)
3351{
3352 /* Report only one error per failed directory load (from the UI
3353 * point of view, not from the CajaDirectory point of view).
3354 * Otherwise you can get multiple identical errors caused by
3355 * unrelated code that just happens to try to iterate this
3356 * directory.
3357 */
3358 if (!view->details->reported_load_error) {
3359 fm_report_error_loading_directory
3360 (fm_directory_view_get_directory_as_file (view),
3361 error,
3362 fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view));
3363 }
3364 view->details->reported_load_error = TRUE(!(0));
3365}

)))))->start_renaming_file) (view, new_file, (0)); } } while

3990static void
3991delayed_rename_file_hack_removed (RenameData *data)

3997
3998static void
3999rename_file (FMDirectoryView *view, CajaFile *new_file)
4000{
4001 /* HACK!!!!
4002 This is a work around bug in listview. After the rename is
4003 enabled we will get file changes due to info about the new
4004 file being read, which will cause the model to change. When
4005 the model changes GtkTreeView clears the editing. This hack just
4006 delays editing for some time to try to avoid this problem.
4007 A major problem is that the selection of the row causes us
4008 to load the slow mimetype for the file, which leads to a
4009 file_changed. So, before we delay we select the row.
4010 */
4011 if (FM_IS_LIST_VIEW (view)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(view)); GType __t = (fm_list_view_get_type()); gboolean __r;
if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) {
4012 RenameData *data;
4013
4014 fm_directory_view_select_file (view, new_file);
4015
4016 data = g_new (RenameData, 1)(RenameData *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (1); gsize
__s = sizeof (RenameData); gpointer __p; if (__s == 1) __p =
g_malloc (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p (__n) &&
(__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L *2UL+1UL) / __s
)) __p = g_malloc (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc_n (__n, __s
); __p; }));
4017 data->view = g_object_ref (view)((__typeof__ (view)) (g_object_ref) (view));
4018 data->new_file = caja_file_ref (new_file);
4019 if (view->details->delayed_rename_file_id != 0) {
4020 g_source_remove (view->details->delayed_rename_file_id);
4021 }
4022 view->details->delayed_rename_file_id =
4023 g_timeout_add_full (G_PRIORITY_DEFAULT0,
4024 100, (GSourceFunc)delayed_rename_file_hack_callback,
4025 data, (GDestroyNotify) delayed_rename_file_hack_removed);
4026
4027 return;
4028 }
4029
4030 /* no need to select because start_renaming_file selects
4031 * fm_directory_view_select_file (view, new_file);
4032 */
4033 EEL_CALL_METHOD (FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW_CLASS, view, start_renaming_file, (view, new_file, FALSE))do { if (((((FMDirectoryViewClass*) (void *) ((((((GObjectClass
*) (((GTypeInstance*) ((view)))->g_class)))))))))->start_renaming_file
!= ((void*)0)) { (* ((((FMDirectoryViewClass*) (void *) ((((
((GObjectClass*) (((GTypeInstance*) ((view)))->g_class))))
)))))->start_renaming_file) (view, new_file, (0)); } } while
(0);
4034 fm_directory_view_reveal_selection (view);
4035}
4036
4037static void
4038reveal_newly_added_folder (FMDirectoryView *view, CajaFile *new_file,
4039 CajaDirectory *directory, GFile *target_location)
4040{
4041 GFile *location;
4042
4043 location = caja_file_get_location (new_file);
4044 if (g_file_equal (location, target_location)) {
4045 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (view,g_signal_handlers_disconnect_matched ((view), (GSignalMatchType

4069static void
4070new_folder_done (GFile *new_folder, gpointer user_data)
4071{
4072 FMDirectoryView *directory_view;
4073 CajaFile *file;
4074 char screen_string[32];
4075 GdkScreen *screen;
4076 NewFolderData *data;
4077
4078 data = (NewFolderData *)user_data;
4079
4080 directory_view = data->directory_view;
4081
4082 if (directory_view == NULL((void*)0)) {
4083 goto fail;
4084 }
4085
4086 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (directory_view,g_signal_handlers_disconnect_matched ((directory_view), (GSignalMatchType
) (G_SIGNAL_MATCH_FUNC | G_SIGNAL_MATCH_DATA), 0, 0, ((void*)
0), (((GCallback) (track_newly_added_locations))), ((void *) data
))
4087 G_CALLBACK (track_newly_added_locations),g_signal_handlers_disconnect_matched ((directory_view), (GSignalMatchType
) (G_SIGNAL_MATCH_FUNC | G_SIGNAL_MATCH_DATA), 0, 0, ((void*)
0), (((GCallback) (track_newly_added_locations))), ((void *) data
))
4088 (void *) data)g_signal_handlers_disconnect_matched ((directory_view), (GSignalMatchType
) (G_SIGNAL_MATCH_FUNC | G_SIGNAL_MATCH_DATA), 0, 0, ((void*)
0), (((GCallback) (track_newly_added_locations))), ((void *) data
));
4089
4090 if (new_folder == NULL((void*)0)) {
4091 goto fail;
4092 }
4093
4094 screen = gtk_widget_get_screen (GTK_WIDGET (directory_view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((directory_view))))));
4095 g_snprintf (screen_string, sizeof (screen_string), "%d", gdk_x11_screen_get_screen_number (screen));
4096
4097 file = caja_file_get (new_folder);
4098 caja_file_set_metadata
4099 (file, CAJA_METADATA_KEY_SCREEN"screen",
4100 NULL((void*)0),
4101 screen_string);
4102
4103 if (g_hash_table_lookup_extended (data->added_locations, new_folder, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0))) {
4104 /* The file was already added */
4105 rename_file (directory_view, file);
4106 } else {
4107 /* We need to run after the default handler adds the folder we want to
4108 * operate on. The ADD_FILE signal is registered as G_SIGNAL_RUN_LAST, so we
4109 * must use connect_after.
4110 */
4111 g_signal_connect_data (directory_view,
4112 "add_file",
4113 G_CALLBACK (reveal_newly_added_folder)((GCallback) (reveal_newly_added_folder)),
4114 g_object_ref (new_folder)((__typeof__ (new_folder)) (g_object_ref) (new_folder)),
4115 (GClosureNotify)g_object_unref,
4116 G_CONNECT_AFTER);
4117 }
4118 caja_file_unref (file);
4119
4120 fail:
4121 g_hash_table_destroy (data->added_locations);
4122 eel_remove_weak_pointer (&data->directory_view);
4123 g_free (data);
4124}

4700{

4865
4866static gboolean
4867search_in_menu_items (GList* items, const char *item_name)
4868{
4869 GList* list;
4870
4871 for (list = items; list != NULL((void*)0); list = list->next) {
4872 CajaMenu* menu;
4873 char *name;
4874
4875 g_object_get (list->data, "name", &name, NULL((void*)0));
4876 if (strcmp (name, item_name) == 0) {
4877 g_free (name);
4878 return TRUE(!(0));
4879 }
4880 g_free (name);
4881
4882 menu = NULL((void*)0);
4883 g_object_get (list->data, "menu", &menu, NULL((void*)0));
4884 if (menu != NULL((void*)0)) {
4885 gboolean ret;
4886 GList* submenus;
4887
4888 submenus = caja_menu_get_items (menu);
4889 ret = search_in_menu_items (submenus, item_name);
4890 caja_menu_item_list_free (submenus);
4891 g_object_unref (menu);
4892 if (ret) {
4893 return TRUE(!(0));
4894 }
4895 }
4896 }
4897 return FALSE(0);
4898}
4899
4900static void
4901extension_action_callback (GtkAction *action,
4902 gpointer callback_data)
4903{
4904 ExtensionActionCallbackData *data;
4905 char *item_name;
4906 gboolean is_valid;
4907 GList *l;
4908 GList *items;
4909
4910 data = callback_data;
4911
4912 /* Make sure the selected menu item is valid for the final sniffed
4913 * mime type */
4914 g_object_get (data->item, "name", &item_name, NULL((void*)0));
4915 items = get_all_extension_menu_items (gtk_widget_get_toplevel (GTK_WIDGET (data->view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((data->view)))))),
4916 data->selection);
4917
4918 is_valid = search_in_menu_items (items, item_name);
4919
4920 for (l = items; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
4921 g_object_unref (l->data);
4922 }
4923 g_list_free (items);
4924
4925 g_free (item_name);
4926
4927 if (is_valid) {
4928 caja_menu_item_activate (data->item);
4929 }
4930}

4947 }
4948 surface = caja_icon_info_get_surface_nodefault_at_size (info, size);
4949 g_object_unref (info);
4950
4951 return surface;
4952}

5038static void
5039add_extension_menu_items (FMDirectoryView *view,
5040 GList *files,
5041 GList *menu_items,
5042 const char *subdirectory)
5043{
5044 GtkUIManager *ui_manager;
5045 GList *l;
5046
5047 ui_manager = caja_window_info_get_ui_manager (view->details->window);
5048
5049 for (l = menu_items; l; l = l->next) {
5050 CajaMenuItem *item;
5051 CajaMenu *menu;
5052 GtkAction *action;
5053 const gchar *action_name;
5054 char *path;
5055
5056 item = CAJA_MENU_ITEM (l->data)((((CajaMenuItem*) (void *) ((l->data)))));
5057
5058 g_object_get (item, "menu", &menu, NULL((void*)0));
5059
5060 action = add_extension_action_for_files (view, item, files);
5061
5062 path = g_build_path ("/", FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW_POPUP_PATH_EXTENSION_ACTIONS"/selection/Extension Actions", subdirectory, NULL((void*)0));
5063 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic push clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
;
5064 action_name = gtk_action_get_name (action);
5065 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic pop ;
5066
5067 gtk_ui_manager_add_ui (ui_manager,
5068 view->details->extensions_menu_merge_id,
5069 path,
5070 action_name,
5071 action_name,
5072 (menu != NULL((void*)0)) ? GTK_UI_MANAGER_MENU : GTK_UI_MANAGER_MENUITEM,
5073 FALSE(0));
5074 g_free (path);
5075
5076 path = g_build_path ("/", FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW_MENU_PATH_EXTENSION_ACTIONS_PLACEHOLDER"/MenuBar/Edit/Extension Actions", subdirectory, NULL((void*)0));
5077 gtk_ui_manager_add_ui (ui_manager,
5078 view->details->extensions_menu_merge_id,
5079 path,
5080 action_name,
5081 action_name,
5082 (menu != NULL((void*)0)) ? GTK_UI_MANAGER_MENU : GTK_UI_MANAGER_MENUITEM,
5083 FALSE(0));
5084 g_free (path);
5085
5086 /* recursively fill the menu */
5087 if (menu != NULL((void*)0)) {
5088 char *subdir;
5089 GList *children;
5090
5091 children = caja_menu_get_items (menu);
5092
5093 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic push clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
;
5094 subdir = g_build_path ("/", subdirectory, gtk_action_get_name (action), NULL((void*)0));
5095 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic pop ;
5096 add_extension_menu_items (view,
5097 files,
5098 children,
5099 subdir);
5100
5101 caja_menu_item_list_free (children);
5102 g_free (subdir);
5103 }
5104 }

5107static void
5108reset_extension_actions_menu (FMDirectoryView *view, GList *selection)
5109{
5110 GList *items;
5111 GtkUIManager *ui_manager;
5112

5117 &view->details->extensions_menu_merge_id,
5118 &view->details->extensions_menu_action_group);
5119
5120 caja_ui_prepare_merge_ui (ui_manager,
5121 "DirExtensionsMenuGroup",
5122 &view->details->extensions_menu_merge_id,
5123 &view->details->extensions_menu_action_group);
5124
5125 items = get_all_extension_menu_items (gtk_widget_get_toplevel (GTK_WIDGET (view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((view)))))),
5126 selection);
5127 if (items != NULL((void*)0)) {
5128 add_extension_menu_items (view, selection, items, "");
5129
5130 g_list_free_full (items, g_object_unref);
5131 }

5134static char *

5136{

5145 if (path != NULL((void*)0)) {

5147 }
5148

5150
5151 return old_path;

5258
5259/* returns newly allocated strings for setting the environment variables */
5260static void
5261get_strings_for_environment_variables (FMDirectoryView *view, GList *selected_files,
5262 char **file_paths, char **uris, char **uri)
5263{
5264 char *directory_uri;
5265
5266 /* We need to check that the directory uri starts with "file:" since
5267 * caja_directory_is_local returns FALSE for nfs.
5268 */
5269 directory_uri = caja_directory_get_uri (view->details->model);
5270 if (eel_str_has_prefix (directory_uri, "file:") ||
5271 eel_uri_is_desktop (directory_uri) ||
5272 eel_uri_is_trash (directory_uri)) {
5273 *file_paths = get_file_paths_as_newline_delimited_string (selected_files);
5274 } else {
5275 *file_paths = g_strdup ("")g_strdup_inline ("");
5276 }
5277 g_free (directory_uri);
5278
5279 *uris = get_file_uris_as_newline_delimited_string (selected_files);
5280
5281 *uri = caja_directory_get_uri (view->details->model);
5282 if (eel_uri_is_desktop (*uri)) {
5283 g_free (*uri);
5284 *uri = caja_get_desktop_directory_uri ();
5285 }
5286}

5289get_directory_view_of_extra_pane (FMDirectoryView *view)
5290{
5291 CajaWindowSlotInfo *slot;
5292
5293 slot = caja_window_info_get_extra_slot (fm_directory_view_get_caja_window (view));
5294 if (slot != NULL((void*)0)) {
5295 CajaView *next_view;
5296
5297 next_view = caja_window_slot_info_get_current_view (slot);
5298
5299 if (FM_IS_DIRECTORY_VIEW (next_view)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(next_view)); GType __t = (fm_directory_view_get_type()); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) {
5300 return FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (next_view)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((next_view)))));
5301 }
5302 }
5303 return NULL((void*)0);
5304}
5305
5306/*
5307 * Set up some environment variables that scripts can use
5308 * to take advantage of the current Caja state.
5309 */
5310static void set_script_environment_variables(FMDirectoryView* view, GList* selected_files)
5311{
5312 char* file_paths;
5313 char* uris;
5314 char* uri;
5315 char* geometry_string;
5316 FMDirectoryView* next_view;
5317
5318 get_strings_for_environment_variables(view, selected_files, &file_paths, &uris, &uri);
5319
5320 g_setenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_SELECTED_FILE_PATHS", file_paths, TRUE(!(0)));
5321 g_setenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_SELECTED_FILE_PATHS", file_paths, TRUE(!(0))); // compatibilidad GNOME
5322
5323 g_free(file_paths);
5324
5325 g_setenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_SELECTED_URIS", uris, TRUE(!(0)));
5326 g_setenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_SELECTED_URIS", uris, TRUE(!(0))); // compatibilidad GNOME
5327
5328 g_free(uris);
5329
5330 g_setenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_CURRENT_URI", uri, TRUE(!(0)));
5331 g_setenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_CURRENT_URI", uri, TRUE(!(0))); // compatibilidad GNOME
5332
5333 g_free(uri);
5334
5335 geometry_string = eel_gtk_window_get_geometry_string(GTK_WINDOW (fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view))((((GtkWindow*) (void *) ((fm_directory_view_get_containing_window
(view)))))));
5336
5337 g_setenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_WINDOW_GEOMETRY", geometry_string, TRUE(!(0)));
5338 g_setenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_WINDOW_GEOMETRY", geometry_string, TRUE(!(0))); // compatibilidad GNOME
5339
5340 g_free(geometry_string);
5341
5342 /* next pane */
5343 next_view = get_directory_view_of_extra_pane(view);
5344
5345 if (next_view)
5346 {
5347 GList* next_pane_selected_files = fm_directory_view_get_selection (next_view);
5348
5349 get_strings_for_environment_variables(next_view, next_pane_selected_files, &file_paths, &uris, &uri);
5350
5351 caja_file_list_free(next_pane_selected_files);
5352 }
5353 else
5354 {
5355 file_paths = g_strdup("")g_strdup_inline ("");
5356 uris = g_strdup("")g_strdup_inline ("");
5357 uri = g_strdup("")g_strdup_inline ("");
5358 }
5359
5360 g_setenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_NEXT_PANE_SELECTED_FILE_PATHS", file_paths, TRUE(!(0)));
5361 g_setenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_NEXT_PANE_SELECTED_FILE_PATHS", file_paths, TRUE(!(0))); // compatibilidad GNOME
5362 g_free(file_paths);
5363
5364 g_setenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_NEXT_PANE_SELECTED_URIS", uris, TRUE(!(0)));
5365 g_setenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_NEXT_PANE_SELECTED_URIS", uris, TRUE(!(0))); // compatibilidad GNOME
5366 g_free(uris);
5367
5368 g_setenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_NEXT_PANE_CURRENT_URI", uri, TRUE(!(0)));
5369 g_setenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_NEXT_PANE_CURRENT_URI", uri, TRUE(!(0))); // compatibilidad GNOME
5370 g_free(uri);
5371}

5375{
5376 g_unsetenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_SELECTED_FILE_PATHS");
5377 g_unsetenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_SELECTED_FILE_PATHS");

5380 g_unsetenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_SELECTED_URIS");
5381
5382 g_unsetenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_CURRENT_URI");
5383 g_unsetenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_CURRENT_URI");
5384
5385 g_unsetenv("CAJA_SCRIPT_WINDOW_GEOMETRY");
5386 g_unsetenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_WINDOW_GEOMETRY");
5387

5389 g_unsetenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_NEXT_PANE_SELECTED_FILE_PATHS");
5390

5392 g_unsetenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_NEXT_PANE_SELECTED_URIS");
5393

5395 g_unsetenv("NAUTILUS_SCRIPT_NEXT_PANE_CURRENT_URI");
5396}
5397
5398static void
5399run_script_callback (GtkAction *action, gpointer callback_data)
5400{
5401 ScriptLaunchParameters *launch_parameters;
5402 GdkScreen *screen;
5403 GList *selected_files;
5404 char *file_uri;
5405 char *local_file_path;
5406 char *quoted_path;
5407 char *old_working_dir;
5408 char **parameters, *name;
5409 GtkWindow *window;
5410
5411 launch_parameters = (ScriptLaunchParameters *) callback_data;
5412
5413 file_uri = caja_file_get_uri (launch_parameters->file);
5414 local_file_path = g_filename_from_uri (file_uri, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
5415 g_assert (local_file_path != NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_261
; if (local_file_path != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_261 = 1; else
_g_boolean_var_261 = 0; _g_boolean_var_261; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c", 5415, ((const char*) (
__func__)), "local_file_path != NULL"); } while (0);
5416 g_free (file_uri);
5417
5418 quoted_path = g_shell_quote (local_file_path);
5419
5420 old_working_dir = change_to_view_directory (launch_parameters->directory_view);
5421
5422 selected_files = fm_directory_view_get_selection (launch_parameters->directory_view);
5423 set_script_environment_variables (launch_parameters->directory_view, selected_files);
5424
5425 parameters = get_file_names_as_parameter_array (selected_files,
5426 launch_parameters->directory_view->details->model);
5427
5428 screen = gtk_widget_get_screen (GTK_WIDGET (launch_parameters->directory_view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((launch_parameters->directory_view
))))));
5429
5430 name = caja_file_get_name (launch_parameters->file);
5431 /* FIXME: handle errors with dialog? Or leave up to each script? */
5432 window = fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (launch_parameters->directory_view);
5433 caja_debug_log (FALSE(0), CAJA_DEBUG_LOG_DOMAIN_USER"USER",
5434 "directory view run_script_callback, window=%p, name=\"%s\", script_path=\"%s\" (omitting script parameters)",
5435 window, name, local_file_path);
5436 caja_launch_application_from_command_array (screen, name, quoted_path, FALSE(0),
5437 (const char * const *) parameters);
5438 g_free (local_file_path);

5558
5559static gboolean
5560directory_belongs_in_scripts_menu (const char *uri)
5561{
5562 int num_levels;
5563 int i;
5564
5565 if (!eel_str_has_prefix (uri, scripts_directory_uri)) {
5566 return FALSE(0);
5567 }
5568
5569 num_levels = 0;
5570 for (i = scripts_directory_uri_length; uri[i] != '\0'; i++) {
5571 if (uri[i] == '/') {
5572 num_levels++;
5573 }
5574 }
5575
5576 if (num_levels > MAX_MENU_LEVELS5) {
5577 return FALSE(0);
5578 }
5579
5580 return TRUE(!(0));
5581}
5582
5583static gboolean
5584update_directory_in_scripts_menu (FMDirectoryView *view, CajaDirectory *directory)
5585{
5586 char *menu_path, *popup_path, *popup_bg_path;
5587 GList *file_list, *filtered, *node;
5588 gboolean any_scripts;
5589 CajaDirectory *dir;
5590 char *uri;
5591 char *escaped_path;
5592 CajaFile *file = NULL((void*)0);
5593
5594 uri = caja_directory_get_uri (directory);
5595 escaped_path = escape_action_path (uri + scripts_directory_uri_length);
5596 g_free (uri);
5597 menu_path = g_strconcat (FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW_MENU_PATH_SCRIPTS_PLACEHOLDER"/MenuBar/File/Open Placeholder/Scripts/Scripts Placeholder",
5598 escaped_path,
5599 NULL((void*)0));
5600 popup_path = g_strconcat (FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW_POPUP_PATH_SCRIPTS_PLACEHOLDER"/selection/Open Placeholder/Scripts/Scripts Placeholder",
5601 escaped_path,
5602 NULL((void*)0));
5603 popup_bg_path = g_strconcat (FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW_POPUP_PATH_BACKGROUND_SCRIPTS_PLACEHOLDER"/background/Before Zoom Items/New Object Items/Scripts/Scripts Placeholder",
5604 escaped_path,
5605 NULL((void*)0));
5606 g_free (escaped_path);
5607
5608 file_list = caja_directory_get_file_list (directory);
5609 filtered = caja_file_list_filter_hidden (file_list, FALSE(0));
5610 caja_file_list_free (file_list);
5611
5612 file_list = caja_file_list_sort_by_display_name (filtered);
5613
5614 any_scripts = FALSE(0);
5615 for (node = file_list; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
5616 file = node->data;
5617
5618 if (caja_file_is_launchable (file)) {
5619 add_script_to_scripts_menus (view, file, menu_path, popup_path, popup_bg_path);
5620 any_scripts = TRUE(!(0));
5621 } else if (caja_file_is_directory (file)) {
5622 uri = caja_file_get_uri (file);
5623 if (directory_belongs_in_scripts_menu (uri)) {
5624 dir = caja_directory_get_by_uri (uri);
5625 add_directory_to_scripts_directory_list (view, dir);
5626 caja_directory_unref (dir);
5627
5628 add_submenu_to_directory_menus (view,
5629 view->details->scripts_action_group,
5630 view->details->scripts_merge_id,
5631 file, menu_path, popup_path, popup_bg_path);
5632
5633 any_scripts = TRUE(!(0));
5634 }
5635 g_free (uri);
5636 }
5637 }
5638
5639 caja_file_list_free (file_list);
5640
5641 g_free (popup_path);
5642 g_free (popup_bg_path);
5643 g_free (menu_path);
5644
5645 return any_scripts;
5646}
5647
5648static void
5649update_scripts_menu (FMDirectoryView *view)
5650{
5651 gboolean any_scripts;
5652 GList *sorted_copy, *node;
5653 GtkUIManager *ui_manager;
5654 GtkAction *action;
5655 CajaDirectory *directory = NULL((void*)0);
5656
5657 /* There is a race condition here. If we don't mark the scripts menu as
5658 valid before we begin our task then we can lose script menu updates that
5659 occur before we finish. */
5660 view->details->scripts_invalid = FALSE(0);
5661
5662 ui_manager = caja_window_info_get_ui_manager (view->details->window);
5663 caja_ui_unmerge_ui (ui_manager,
5664 &view->details->scripts_merge_id,
5665 &view->details->scripts_action_group);
5666
5667 caja_ui_prepare_merge_ui (ui_manager,
5668 "ScriptsGroup",
5669 &view->details->scripts_merge_id,
5670 &view->details->scripts_action_group);
5671
5672 /* As we walk through the directories, remove any that no longer belong. */
5673 any_scripts = FALSE(0);
5674 sorted_copy = caja_directory_list_sort_by_uri
5675 (caja_directory_list_copy (view->details->scripts_directory_list));
5676 for (node = sorted_copy; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
5677 char *uri;
5678
5679 directory = node->data;
5680
5681 uri = caja_directory_get_uri (directory);
5682 if (!directory_belongs_in_scripts_menu (uri)) {
5683 remove_directory_from_scripts_directory_list (view, directory);
5684 } else if (update_directory_in_scripts_menu (view, directory)) {
5685 any_scripts = TRUE(!(0));
5686 }
5687 g_free (uri);
5688 }
5689 caja_directory_list_free (sorted_copy);
5690
5691 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic push clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
;
5692 action = gtk_action_group_get_action (view->details->dir_action_group, FM_ACTION_SCRIPTS"Scripts");
5693 gtk_action_set_visible (action, any_scripts);
5694 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic pop ;
5695}

5842static gboolean
5843update_directory_in_templates_menu (FMDirectoryView *view,
5844 const char *templates_directory_uri,
5845 CajaDirectory *directory)
5846{
5847 char *menu_path, *popup_bg_path;
5848 GList *file_list, *filtered, *node;
5849 gboolean any_templates;
5850 CajaDirectory *dir;
5851 char *escaped_path;
5852 char *uri;
5853 int num;
5854 CajaFile *file = NULL((void*)0);
5855
5856 /* We know this directory belongs to the template dir, so it must exist */
5857 g_assert (templates_directory_uri)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_263
; if (templates_directory_uri) _g_boolean_var_263 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_263
= 0; _g_boolean_var_263; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c", 5857, ((const char*) (
__func__)), "templates_directory_uri"); } while (0);

5860 escaped_path = escape_action_path (uri + strlen (templates_directory_uri));
5861 g_free (uri);
5862 menu_path = g_strconcat (FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW_MENU_PATH_NEW_DOCUMENTS_PLACEHOLDER"/MenuBar/File/New Items Placeholder/New Documents/New Documents Placeholder",

5866 escaped_path,

5879 file = node->data;
5880

5928 occur before we finish. */

5944 (caja_directory_list_copy (view->details->templates_directory_list));

6004static GtkMenu *
6005create_popup_menu (FMDirectoryView *view, const char *popup_path)
6006{
6007 GtkWidget *menu;
6008
6009 menu = gtk_ui_manager_get_widget (caja_window_info_get_ui_manager (view->details->window),
6010 popup_path);
6011 gtk_menu_set_screen (GTK_MENU (menu)((((GtkMenu*) (void *) ((menu))))),
6012 gtk_widget_get_screen (GTK_WIDGET (view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((view)))))));
6013 gtk_widget_show (GTK_WIDGET (menu)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((menu))))));
6014
6015 return GTK_MENU (menu)((((GtkMenu*) (void *) ((menu)))));
6016}
6017
6018static void
6019copy_or_cut_files (FMDirectoryView *view,
6020 GList *clipboard_contents,
6021 gboolean cut)
6022{
6023 int count;
6024 char *status_string;
6025 CajaClipboardInfo info;
6026 GtkTargetList *target_list;
6027 GtkTargetEntry *targets;
6028 int n_targets;
6029
6030 info.files = clipboard_contents;
6031 info.cut = cut;
6032
6033 target_list = gtk_target_list_new (NULL((void*)0), 0);
6034 gtk_target_list_add (target_list, copied_files_atom, 0, 0);
6035 gtk_target_list_add_uri_targets (target_list, 0);
6036 gtk_target_list_add_text_targets (target_list, 0);
6037
6038 targets = gtk_target_table_new_from_list (target_list, &n_targets);
6039 gtk_target_list_unref (target_list);
6040
6041 gtk_clipboard_set_with_data (caja_clipboard_get (GTK_WIDGET (view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((view)))))),
6042 targets, n_targets,
6043 caja_get_clipboard_callback, caja_clear_clipboard_callback,
6044 NULL((void*)0));
6045 gtk_target_table_free (targets, n_targets);
6046
6047 caja_clipboard_monitor_set_clipboard_info (caja_clipboard_monitor_get (), &info);
6048
6049 count = g_list_length (clipboard_contents);
6050 if (count == 1) {
6051 char *name;
6052
6053 name = caja_file_get_display_name (clipboard_contents->data);
6054 if (cut) {
6055 status_string = g_strdup_printf (_("\"%s\" will be moved "dcgettext (((void*)0), "\"%s\" will be moved " "if you select the Paste command"
, 5)
6056 "if you select the Paste command")dcgettext (((void*)0), "\"%s\" will be moved " "if you select the Paste command"
, 5),
6057 name);
6058 } else {
6059 status_string = g_strdup_printf (_("\"%s\" will be copied "dcgettext (((void*)0), "\"%s\" will be copied " "if you select the Paste command"
, 5)
6060 "if you select the Paste command")dcgettext (((void*)0), "\"%s\" will be copied " "if you select the Paste command"
, 5),
6061 name);
6062 }
6063 g_free (name);
6064 } else {
6065 if (cut) {
6066 status_string = g_strdup_printf (ngettext("The %'d selected item will be moved "dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5)
6067 "if you select the Paste command",dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5)
6068 "The %'d selected items will be moved "dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5)
6069 "if you select the Paste command",dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5)
6070 count)dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be moved "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5),
6071 count);
6072 } else {
6073 status_string = g_strdup_printf (ngettext("The %'d selected item will be copied "dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5)
6074 "if you select the Paste command",dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5)
6075 "The %'d selected items will be copied "dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5)
6076 "if you select the Paste command",dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5)
6077 count)dcngettext (((void*)0), "The %'d selected item will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", "The %'d selected items will be copied "
"if you select the Paste command", count, 5),
6078 count);
6079 }
6080 }
6081
6082 caja_window_slot_info_set_status (view->details->slot,
6083 status_string);
6084 g_free (status_string);
6085}
6086
6087static void
6088action_copy_files_callback (GtkAction *action,
6089 gpointer callback_data)
6090{
6091 FMDirectoryView *view;
6092 GList *selection;
6093
6094 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (callback_data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((callback_data)))));
6095
6096 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection_for_file_transfer (view);
6097 copy_or_cut_files (view, selection, FALSE(0));
6098 caja_file_list_free (selection);
6099}
6100
6101static void
6102move_copy_selection_to_location (FMDirectoryView *view,
6103 int copy_action,
6104 char *target_uri)
6105{
6106 GList *selection, *uris, *l;
6107
6108 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection_for_file_transfer (view);
6109 if (selection == NULL((void*)0)) {
6110 return;
6111 }
6112
6113 uris = NULL((void*)0);
6114 for (l = selection; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
6115 uris = g_list_prepend (uris,
6116 caja_file_get_uri ((CajaFile *) l->data));
6117 }
6118 uris = g_list_reverse (uris);
6119
6120 fm_directory_view_move_copy_items (uris, NULL((void*)0), target_uri,
6121 copy_action,
6122 0, 0,
6123 view);
6124
6125 g_list_free_full (uris, g_free);
6126 caja_file_list_free (selection);
6127}

6239static void
6240paste_clipboard_data (FMDirectoryView *view,
6241 GtkSelectionData *selection_data,
6242 char *destination_uri)
6243{
6244 gboolean cut;
6245 GList *item_uris;
6246
6247 cut = FALSE(0);
6248 item_uris = caja_clipboard_get_uri_list_from_selection_data (selection_data, &cut,
6249 copied_files_atom);
6250
6251 if (item_uris == NULL((void*)0)|| destination_uri == NULL((void*)0)) {
6252 caja_window_slot_info_set_status (view->details->slot,
6253 _("There is nothing on the clipboard to paste.")dcgettext (((void*)0), "There is nothing on the clipboard to paste."
, 5));
6254 } else {
6255 fm_directory_view_move_copy_items (item_uris, NULL((void*)0), destination_uri,
6256 cut ? GDK_ACTION_MOVE : GDK_ACTION_COPY,
6257 0, 0,
6258 view);
6259
6260 /* If items are cut then remove from clipboard */
6261 if (cut) {
6262 gtk_clipboard_clear (caja_clipboard_get (GTK_WIDGET (view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((view)))))));
6263 }
6264
6265 g_list_free_full (item_uris, g_free);
6266 }
6267}

6269static void
6270paste_clipboard_received_callback (GtkClipboard *clipboard,
6271 GtkSelectionData *selection_data,
6272 gpointer data)
6273{
6274 FMDirectoryView *view;
6275 char *view_uri;
6276
6277 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((data)))));
6278
6279 view_uri = fm_directory_view_get_backing_uri (view);
6280
6281 if (view->details->window != NULL((void*)0)) {
6282 paste_clipboard_data (view, selection_data, view_uri);
6283 }
6284
6285 g_free (view_uri);
6286
6287 g_object_unref (view);
6288}

6622 error->code != G_IO_ERROR_FAILED_HANDLED &&
6623 error->code != G_IO_ERROR_ALREADY_MOUNTED))) {
6624 eel_show_error_dialog (_("Unable to start location")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Unable to start location", 5),
6625 error->message, NULL((void*)0));
6626 }

6637
6638 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((data)))));
6639
6640 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection (view);
6641 for (l = selection; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
6642 file = CAJA_FILE (l->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((l->data)))));
6643

6645 mount_op = gtk_mount_operation_new (fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view));
6646 caja_file_start (file, mount_op, NULL((void*)0),
6647 file_start_callback, NULL((void*)0));

6649 }
6650 }

6988 int response_id,
6989 gpointer data)
6990{
6991#ifdef GIO_CONVERSION_DONE
6992 GtkEntry *entry;
6993 char *uri;
6994 const char *name;
6995 char *icon;
6996
6997 entry = GTK_ENTRY (data)((((GtkEntry*) (void *) ((data)))));
6998
6999 switch (response_id) {
7000 case GTK_RESPONSE_OK:
7001 uri = g_object_get_data (G_OBJECT (dialog)((((GObject*) (void *) ((dialog))))), "link-uri");
7002 icon = g_object_get_data (G_OBJECT (dialog)((((GObject*) (void *) ((dialog))))), "link-icon");
7003 name = gtk_entry_get_text (entry);
7004 mate_vfs_connect_to_server (uri, (char *)name, icon);
7005 gtk_widget_destroy (GTK_WIDGET (dialog)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((dialog))))));
7006 break;
7007 case GTK_RESPONSE_NONE:
7008 case GTK_RESPONSE_DELETE_EVENT:
7009 case GTK_RESPONSE_CANCEL:
7010 gtk_widget_destroy (GTK_WIDGET (dialog)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((dialog))))));
7011 break;
7012 default :
7013 g_assert_not_reached ()do { g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c"
, 7013, ((const char*) (__func__)), ((void*)0)); } while (0);
7014 }
7015#endif
7016 /* FIXME: the above code should make a server connection permanent */
7017 gtk_widget_destroy (GTK_WIDGET (dialog)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((dialog))))));
7018}

7294
7295static void
7296fm_directory_view_init_show_hidden_files (FMDirectoryView *view)
7297{
7298 CajaWindowShowHiddenFilesMode mode;
7299 gboolean show_hidden_changed;
7300 gboolean show_hidden_default_setting;
7301
7302 if (view->details->ignore_hidden_file_preferences) {
7303 return;
7304 }
7305
7306 show_hidden_changed = FALSE(0);
7307 mode = caja_window_info_get_hidden_files_mode (view->details->window);
7308
7309 if (mode == CAJA_WINDOW_SHOW_HIDDEN_FILES_DEFAULT) {
7310 show_hidden_default_setting = g_settings_get_boolean (caja_preferences, CAJA_PREFERENCES_SHOW_HIDDEN_FILES"show-hidden-files");
7311 if (show_hidden_default_setting != view->details->show_hidden_files) {
7312 view->details->show_hidden_files = show_hidden_default_setting;
7313 show_hidden_changed = TRUE(!(0));
7314 }
7315 } else {
7316 if (mode == CAJA_WINDOW_SHOW_HIDDEN_FILES_ENABLE) {
7317 show_hidden_changed = !view->details->show_hidden_files;
7318 view->details->show_hidden_files = TRUE(!(0));
7319 } else {
7320 show_hidden_changed = view->details->show_hidden_files;
7321 view->details->show_hidden_files = FALSE(0);
7322 }
7323 }
7324
7325 if (show_hidden_changed && (view->details->model != NULL((void*)0))) {
7326 load_directory (view, view->details->model);
7327 }
7328
7329}
7330
7331static void
7332fm_directory_view_init_show_backup_files (FMDirectoryView *view)
7333{
7334 CajaWindowShowBackupFilesMode mode;
7335 gboolean show_backup_changed;
7336 gboolean show_backup_default_setting;
7337
7338 show_backup_changed = FALSE(0);
7339 mode = caja_window_info_get_backup_files_mode (view->details->window);
7340
7341 if (mode == CAJA_WINDOW_SHOW_BACKUP_FILES_DEFAULT) {
7342 show_backup_default_setting = g_settings_get_boolean (caja_preferences, CAJA_PREFERENCES_SHOW_BACKUP_FILES"show-backup-files");
7343 if (show_backup_default_setting != view->details->show_backup_files) {
7344 view->details->show_backup_files = show_backup_default_setting;
7345 show_backup_changed = TRUE(!(0));
7346 }
7347 } else {
7348 if (mode == CAJA_WINDOW_SHOW_BACKUP_FILES_ENABLE) {
7349 show_backup_changed = !view->details->show_backup_files;
7350 view->details->show_backup_files = TRUE(!(0));
7351 } else {
7352 show_backup_changed = view->details->show_backup_files;
7353 view->details->show_backup_files = FALSE(0);
7354 }
7355 }
7356
7357 if (show_backup_changed && (view->details->model != NULL((void*)0))) {
7358 load_directory (view, view->details->model);
7359 }
7360
7361}
