7678static void
7679connect_proxy (FMDirectoryView *view,
7680 GtkAction *action,
7681 GtkWidget *proxy,
7682 GtkActionGroup *action_group)
7683{
7684 const gchar *action_name;
7685
7686 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic push clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
;
7687 action_name = gtk_action_get_name (action);
7688 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic pop ;
7689
7690 if (strcmp (action_name, FM_ACTION_NEW_EMPTY_FILE"New Empty File") == 0 &&
7691 GTK_IS_IMAGE_MENU_ITEM (proxy)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(proxy)); GType __t = ((gtk_image_menu_item_get_type ())); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) {
7692 cairo_surface_t *surface;
7693
7694 surface = get_menu_icon ("text-x-generic", GTK_WIDGET (view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((view))))));
7695
7696 if (surface != NULL((void*)0)) {
7697 GtkWidget *image;
7698
7699 image = gtk_image_new_from_surface (surface);
7700 gtk_image_menu_item_set_image (GTK_IMAGE_MENU_ITEM (proxy)((((GtkImageMenuItem*) (void *) ((proxy))))), image);
7701
7702 cairo_surface_destroy (surface);
7703 }
7704 }
7705}
7706
7707static void
7708pre_activate (FMDirectoryView *view,
7709 GtkAction *action,
7710 GtkActionGroup *action_group)
7711{
7712 GdkEvent *event;
7713 GtkWidget *proxy;
7714 gboolean activated_from_popup;
7715
7716 /* check whether action was activated through a popup menu.
7717 * If not, unset the last stored context menu popup position */
7718 activated_from_popup = FALSE(0);
7719
7720 event = gtk_get_current_event ();
7721 proxy = gtk_get_event_widget (event);
7722
7723 if (proxy != NULL((void*)0)) {
7724 GtkWidget *toplevel;
7725 GdkWindowTypeHint hint;
7726
7727 toplevel = gtk_widget_get_toplevel (proxy);
7728
7729 if (GTK_IS_WINDOW (toplevel)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(toplevel)); GType __t = ((gtk_window_get_type ())); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) {
7730 hint = gtk_window_get_type_hint (GTK_WINDOW (toplevel)((((GtkWindow*) (void *) ((toplevel))))));
7731
7732 if (hint == GDK_WINDOW_TYPE_HINT_POPUP_MENU) {
7733 activated_from_popup = TRUE(!(0));
7734 }
7735 }
7736 }
7737
7738 if (!activated_from_popup) {
7739 update_context_menu_position_from_event (view, NULL((void*)0));
7740 }
7741}

7743static void
7744real_merge_menus (FMDirectoryView *view)
7745{
7746 GtkActionGroup *action_group;
7747 GtkUIManager *ui_manager;
7748 GtkAction *action;
7749 const char *ui;
7750 char *tooltip;
7751
7752 ui_manager = caja_window_info_get_ui_manager (view->details->window);
7753
7754 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic push clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
;
7755 action_group = gtk_action_group_new ("DirViewActions");
7756#ifdef ENABLE_NLS1
7757 gtk_action_group_set_translation_domain (action_group, GETTEXT_PACKAGE"caja");
7758#endif /* ENABLE_NLS */
7759 view->details->dir_action_group = action_group;
7760 gtk_action_group_add_actions (action_group,
7761 directory_view_entries, G_N_ELEMENTS (directory_view_entries)(sizeof (directory_view_entries) / sizeof ((directory_view_entries
)[0])),
7762 view);
7763 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic pop ;
7764
7765 /* Translators: %s is a directory */
7766 tooltip = g_strdup_printf(_("Run or manage scripts from %s")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Run or manage scripts from %s", 5), "~/.config/caja/scripts");
7767 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic push clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
;
7768 /* Create a script action here specially because its tooltip is dynamic */
7769 action = gtk_action_new ("Scripts", _("_Scripts")dcgettext (((void*)0), "_Scripts", 5), tooltip, NULL((void*)0));
7770 gtk_action_group_add_action (action_group, action);
7771 g_object_unref (action);
7772 g_free (tooltip);
7773
7774 action = gtk_action_group_get_action (action_group, FM_ACTION_NO_TEMPLATES"No Templates");
7775 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action, FALSE(0));
7776 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic pop ;
7777
7778 g_signal_connect_object (action_group, "connect-proxy",
7779 G_CALLBACK (connect_proxy)((GCallback) (connect_proxy)), G_OBJECT (view)((((GObject*) (void *) ((view))))),
7780 G_CONNECT_SWAPPED);
7781 g_signal_connect_object (action_group, "pre-activate",
7782 G_CALLBACK (pre_activate)((GCallback) (pre_activate)), G_OBJECT (view)((((GObject*) (void *) ((view))))),
7783 G_CONNECT_SWAPPED);
7784
7785 /* Insert action group at end so clipboard action group ends up before it */
7786 gtk_ui_manager_insert_action_group (ui_manager, action_group, -1);
7787 g_object_unref (action_group); /* owned by ui manager */
7788
7789 ui = caja_ui_string_get ("caja-directory-view-ui.xml");
7790 view->details->dir_merge_id = gtk_ui_manager_add_ui_from_string (ui_manager, ui, -1, NULL((void*)0));
7791 g_signal_connect_object (fm_directory_view_get_background (view), "settings_changed",
7792 G_CALLBACK (schedule_update_menus)((GCallback) (schedule_update_menus)), G_OBJECT (view)((((GObject*) (void *) ((view))))),
7793 G_CONNECT_SWAPPED);
7794 view->details->scripts_invalid = TRUE(!(0));
7795 view->details->templates_invalid = TRUE(!(0));
7796}
7797
7798static gboolean
7799can_paste_into_file (CajaFile *file)
7800{
7801 if (caja_file_is_directory (file) &&
7802 caja_file_can_write (file)) {
7803 return TRUE(!(0));
7804 }
7805 if (caja_file_has_activation_uri (file)) {
7806 GFile *location;
7807 CajaFile *activation_file;
7808 gboolean res;
7809
7810 location = caja_file_get_activation_location (file);
7811 activation_file = caja_file_get (location);
7812 g_object_unref (location);
7813
7814 /* The target location might not have data for it read yet,
7815 and we can't want to do sync I/O, so treat the unknown
7816 case as can-write */
7817 res = (caja_file_get_file_type (activation_file) == G_FILE_TYPE_UNKNOWN) ||
7818 (caja_file_get_file_type (activation_file) == G_FILE_TYPE_DIRECTORY &&
7819 caja_file_can_write (activation_file));
7820
7821 caja_file_unref (activation_file);
7822
7823 return res;
7824 }
7825
7826 return FALSE(0);
7827}
7828
7829static void
7830clipboard_targets_received (GtkClipboard *clipboard,
7831 GdkAtom *targets,
7832 int n_targets,
7833 gpointer user_data)
7834{
7835 FMDirectoryView *view;
7836 gboolean can_paste;
7837 GList *selection;
7838 int count;
7839 GtkAction *action;
7840
7841 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (user_data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((user_data)))));
7842 can_paste = FALSE(0);
7843
7844 if (view->details->window == NULL((void*)0) ||
7845 !view->details->active) {
7846 /* We've been destroyed or became inactive since call */
7847 g_object_unref (view);
7848 return;
7849 }
7850
7851 if (targets) {
7852 int i;
7853
7854 for (i=0; i < n_targets; i++) {
7855 if (targets[i] == copied_files_atom) {
7856 can_paste = TRUE(!(0));
7857 }
7858 }
7859 }
7860
7861 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection (view);
7862 count = g_list_length (selection);
7863
7864 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic push clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
;
7865 action = gtk_action_group_get_action (view->details->dir_action_group,
7866 FM_ACTION_PASTE"Paste");
7867 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action,
7868 can_paste && !fm_directory_view_is_read_only (view));
7869
7870 action = gtk_action_group_get_action (view->details->dir_action_group,
7871 FM_ACTION_PASTE_FILES_INTO"Paste Files Into");
7872 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action,
7873 can_paste && count == 1 &&
7874 can_paste_into_file (CAJA_FILE (selection->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((selection->data)))))));
7875
7876 action = gtk_action_group_get_action (view->details->dir_action_group,
7877 FM_ACTION_LOCATION_PASTE_FILES_INTO"LocationPasteFilesInto");
7878 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic pop ;
7879 g_object_set_data (G_OBJECT (action)((((GObject*) (void *) ((action))))),
7880 "can-paste-according-to-clipboard",
7881 GINT_TO_POINTER (can_paste)((gpointer) (glong) (can_paste)));
7882 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic push clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
;
7883 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action,
7884 GPOINTER_TO_INT (g_object_get_data (G_OBJECT (action),((gint) (glong) (g_object_get_data (((((GObject*) (void *) ((
action))))), "can-paste-according-to-clipboard")))
7885 "can-paste-according-to-clipboard"))((gint) (glong) (g_object_get_data (((((GObject*) (void *) ((
action))))), "can-paste-according-to-clipboard"))) &&
7886 GPOINTER_TO_INT (g_object_get_data (G_OBJECT (action),((gint) (glong) (g_object_get_data (((((GObject*) (void *) ((
action))))), "can-paste-according-to-destination")))
7887 "can-paste-according-to-destination"))((gint) (glong) (g_object_get_data (((((GObject*) (void *) ((
action))))), "can-paste-according-to-destination"))));
7888 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONSclang diagnostic pop ;
7889
7890 caja_file_list_free (selection);
7891
7892 g_object_unref (view);
7893}
7894
7895static gboolean
7896showing_trash_directory (FMDirectoryView *view)
7897{
7898 CajaFile *file;
7899
7900 file = fm_directory_view_get_directory_as_file (view);
7901 if (file != NULL((void*)0)) {
7902 return caja_file_is_in_trash (file);
7903 }
7904 return FALSE(0);
7905}
7906
7907static gboolean
7908should_show_empty_trash (FMDirectoryView *view)
7909{
7910 return (showing_trash_directory (view) || caja_window_info_get_window_type (view->details->window) == CAJA_WINDOW_NAVIGATION);
7911}
7912
7913static gboolean
7914file_list_all_are_folders (GList *file_list)
7915{
7916 GList *l;
7917 char *activation_uri;
7918 gboolean is_dir;
7919 CajaFile *linked_file;
7920 CajaFile *file = NULL((void*)0);
7921
7922 for (l = file_list; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
7923 file = CAJA_FILE (l->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((l->data)))));
7924 if (caja_file_is_caja_link (file) &&
7925 !CAJA_IS_DESKTOP_ICON_FILE (file)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(file)); GType __t = (caja_desktop_icon_file_get_type()); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) {
7926 if (caja_file_is_launcher (file)) {
7927 return FALSE(0);
7928 }
7929
7930 activation_uri = caja_file_get_activation_uri (file);
7931
7932 if (activation_uri == NULL((void*)0)) {
7933 g_free (activation_uri);
7934 return FALSE(0);
7935 }
7936
7937 linked_file = caja_file_get_existing_by_uri (activation_uri);
7938
7939 /* We might not actually know the type of the linked file yet,
7940 * however we don't want to schedule a read, since that might do things
7941 * like ask for password etc. This is a bit unfortunate, but I don't
7942 * know any way around it, so we do various heuristics here
7943 * to get things mostly right
7944 */
7945 is_dir =
7946 (linked_file != NULL((void*)0) &&
7947 caja_file_is_directory (linked_file)) ||
7948 (activation_uri != NULL((void*)0) &&
7949 activation_uri[strlen (activation_uri) - 1] == '/');
7950
7951 caja_file_unref (linked_file);
7952 g_free (activation_uri);
7953
7954 if (!is_dir) {
7955 return FALSE(0);
7956 }
7957 } else if (!(caja_file_is_directory (file) ||
7958 CAJA_IS_DESKTOP_ICON_FILE (file)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(file)); GType __t = (caja_desktop_icon_file_get_type()); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; })))))) {
7959 return FALSE(0);
7960 }
7961 }
7962 return TRUE(!(0));
7963}

7965static void
7966file_should_show_foreach (CajaFile *file,
7967 gboolean *show_mount,
7968 gboolean *show_unmount,
7969 gboolean *show_eject,
7970 gboolean *show_connect,
7971 gboolean *show_format,
7972 gboolean *show_start,
7973 gboolean *show_stop,
7974 gboolean *show_poll,
7975 GDriveStartStopType *start_stop_type)
7976{
7977 *show_mount = FALSE(0);
7978 *show_unmount = FALSE(0);
7979 *show_eject = FALSE(0);
7980 *show_connect = FALSE(0);
7981 *show_format = FALSE(0);
7982 *show_start = FALSE(0);
7983 *show_stop = FALSE(0);
7984 *show_poll = FALSE(0);
7985
7986 if (caja_file_can_eject (file)) {
7987 *show_eject = TRUE(!(0));
7988 }
7989
7990 if (caja_file_can_mount (file)) {
7991 *show_mount = TRUE(!(0));
7992
7993#ifdef TODO_GIO
7994 if (something &&
7995 g_find_program_in_path ("gfloppy")) {
7996 *show_format = TRUE(!(0));
7997 }
7998#endif
7999 }
8000
8001 if (caja_file_can_start (file) || caja_file_can_start_degraded (file)) {
8002 *show_start = TRUE(!(0));
8003 }
8004
8005 if (caja_file_can_stop (file)) {
8006 *show_stop = TRUE(!(0));
8007 }
8008
8009 /* Dot not show both Unmount and Eject/Safe Removal; too confusing to
8010 * have too many menu entries */
8011 if (caja_file_can_unmount (file) && !*show_eject && !*show_stop) {
8012 *show_unmount = TRUE(!(0));
8013 }
8014
8015 if (caja_file_can_poll_for_media (file) && !caja_file_is_media_check_automatic (file)) {
8016 *show_poll = TRUE(!(0));
8017 }
8018
8019 *start_stop_type = caja_file_get_start_stop_type (file);
8020
8021 if (caja_file_is_caja_link (file)) {
8022 char *uri;
8023
8024 uri = caja_file_get_activation_uri (file);
8025 if (uri != NULL((void*)0) &&
8026 (eel_istr_has_prefix (uri, "ftp:") ||
8027 eel_istr_has_prefix (uri, "ssh:") ||
8028 eel_istr_has_prefix (uri, "sftp:") ||
8029 eel_istr_has_prefix (uri, "dav:") ||
8030 eel_istr_has_prefix (uri, "davs:"))) {
8031 *show_connect = TRUE(!(0));
8032 }
8033 g_free (uri);
8034 }
8035}

8096static gboolean
8097files_are_all_directories (GList *files)
8098{
8099 GList *l;
8100 gboolean all_directories;
8101 CajaFile *file = NULL((void*)0);
8102
8103 all_directories = TRUE(!(0));
8104
8105 for (l = files; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
8106 file = CAJA_FILE (l->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((l->data)))));
8107 all_directories &= caja_file_is_directory (file);
8108 }
8109
8110 return all_directories;
8111}
8112
8113static gboolean
8114files_is_none_directory (GList *files)
8115{
8116 GList *l;
8117 gboolean no_directory;
8118 CajaFile *file = NULL((void*)0);
8119
8120 no_directory = TRUE(!(0));
8121
8122 for (l = files; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
8123 file = CAJA_FILE (l->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((l->data)))));
8124 no_directory &= !caja_file_is_directory (file);
8125 }
8126
8127 return no_directory;
8128}

8622 can_paste_into_file (CAJA_FILE (selection->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((selection->data)))))));

8788 * Therefore, we don't update the sensitivity of FM_ACTION_LOCATION_PROPERTIES */
8789}
8790
8791static void
8792clipboard_changed_callback (CajaClipboardMonitor *monitor, FMDirectoryView *view)
8793{
8794 GList *selection;
8795 gint selection_count;
8796
8797 if (!view->details->active) {
8798 return;
8799 }
8800
8801 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection (view);
8802 selection_count = g_list_length (selection);
8803
8804 real_update_paste_menu (view, selection, selection_count);
8805
8806 caja_file_list_free (selection);
8807
8808}
8809
8810static gboolean
8811can_delete_all (GList *files)
8812{
8813 GList *l;
8814 CajaFile *file = NULL((void*)0);
8815
8816 for (l = files; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
8817 file = l->data;
8818 if (!caja_file_can_delete (file)) {
8819 return FALSE(0);
8820 }
8821 }
8822 return TRUE(!(0));
8823}
8824
8825static gboolean
8826has_writable_extra_pane (FMDirectoryView *view)
8827{
8828 FMDirectoryView *other_view;
8829
8830 other_view = get_directory_view_of_extra_pane (view);
8831 if (other_view != NULL((void*)0)) {
8832 return !fm_directory_view_is_read_only (other_view);
8833 }
8834 return FALSE(0);
8835}

9487static void
9488schedule_update_menus (FMDirectoryView *view)
9489{
9490 g_assert (FM_IS_DIRECTORY_VIEW (view))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_291
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((view)); GType __t = (fm_directory_view_get_type()); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_291
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_291 = 0; _g_boolean_var_291; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c"
, 9490, ((const char*) (__func__)), "FM_IS_DIRECTORY_VIEW (view)"
); } while (0);
9491
9492 /* Don't schedule updates after destroy (#349551),
9493 * or if we are not active.
9494 */
9495 if (view->details->window == NULL((void*)0) ||

9497 return;
9498 }

9500 view->details->menu_states_untrustworthy = TRUE(!(0));
9501
9502 /* Schedule a menu update with the current update interval */
9503 if (view->details->update_menus_timeout_id == 0) {

9529static void
9530schedule_update_status (FMDirectoryView *view)
9531{
9532 g_assert (FM_IS_DIRECTORY_VIEW (view))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_292
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance

= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_292
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_292 = 0; _g_boolean_var_292; }), 1)

9551/**
9552 * fm_directory_view_notify_selection_changed:
9553 *
9554 * Notify this view that the selection has changed. This is normally
9555 * called only by subclasses.
9556 * @view: FMDirectoryView whose selection has changed.
9557 *
9558 **/
9559void
9560fm_directory_view_notify_selection_changed (FMDirectoryView *view)
9561{
9562 g_return_if_fail (FM_IS_DIRECTORY_VIEW (view))do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_293
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance

__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_293
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_293 = 0; _g_boolean_var_293; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const
char*) (__func__)), "FM_IS_DIRECTORY_VIEW (view)"); return; }
} while (0);
9563
9564 if (caja_debug_log_is_domain_enabled (CAJA_DEBUG_LOG_DOMAIN_USER"USER")) {
9565 GList *selection;
9566 GtkWindow *window;
9567
9568 selection = fm_directory_view_get_selection (view);
9569
9570 window = fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view);
9571 caja_debug_log_with_file_list (FALSE(0), CAJA_DEBUG_LOG_DOMAIN_USER"USER", selection,

9587 view);

9592 } else {
9593 /* Here is the work we do only when we're not
9594 * batching selection changes. In other words, it's the slower
9595 * stuff that we don't want to slow down selection techniques
9596 * such as rubberband-selecting in icon view.
9597 */
9598
9599 /* Schedule an update of menu item states to match selection */
9600 schedule_update_menus (view);
9601 }

); } while (0);

9645 fm_directory_view_stop (view);
9646 fm_directory_view_clear (view);
9647

9649

9651 * location, so they won't have any false lingering knowledge
9652 * of old selection.
9653 */
9654 schedule_update_menus (view);
9655

9657 fm_directory_view_remove_subdirectory (view,
9658 view->details->subdirectory_list->data);
9659 }

9662

9665 view->details->model = directory;

9667

9669 view->details->directory_as_file =

9671 caja_file_unref (old_file);
9672
9673 view->details->reported_load_error = FALSE(0);
9674
9675 /* FIXME bugzilla.gnome.org 45062: In theory, we also need to monitor metadata here (as
9676 * well as doing a call when ready), in case external forces
9677 * change the directory's file metadata.
9678 */
9679 attributes =
9680 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO |
9681 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_MOUNT |
9682 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_FILESYSTEM_INFO;
9683 view->details->metadata_for_directory_as_file_pending = TRUE(!(0));
9684 view->details->metadata_for_files_in_directory_pending = TRUE(!(0));
9685 caja_file_call_when_ready
9686 (view->details->directory_as_file,
9687 attributes,
9688 metadata_for_directory_as_file_ready_callback, view);
9689 caja_directory_call_when_ready
9690 (view->details->model,
9691 attributes,
9692 FALSE(0),
9693 metadata_for_files_in_directory_ready_callback, view);
9694
9695 /* If capabilities change, then we need to update the menus
9696 * because of New Folder, and relative emblems.
9697 */
9698 attributes =
9699 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO |
9700 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_FILESYSTEM_INFO;
9701 caja_file_monitor_add (view->details->directory_as_file,
9702 &view->details->directory_as_file,
9703 attributes);
9704
9705 view->details->file_changed_handler_id = g_signal_connectg_signal_connect_data ((view->details->directory_as_file
), ("changed"), (((GCallback) (file_changed_callback))), (view
), ((void*)0), (GConnectFlags) 0)
9706 (view->details->directory_as_file, "changed",g_signal_connect_data ((view->details->directory_as_file

), ((void*)0), (GConnectFlags) 0)

), ("changed"), (((GCallback) (file_changed_callback))), (view

9710static void
9711finish_loading (FMDirectoryView *view)
9712{
9713 CajaFileAttributes attributes;
9714
9715 caja_window_info_report_load_underway (view->details->window,
9716 CAJA_VIEW (view)((((CajaView*) (void *) ((view))))));
9717
9718 /* Tell interested parties that we've begun loading this directory now.
9719 * Subclasses use this to know that the new metadata is now available.
9720 */
9721 fm_directory_view_begin_loading (view);
9722
9723 /* Assume we have now all information to show window */
9724 caja_window_info_view_visible (view->details->window, CAJA_VIEW (view)((((CajaView*) (void *) ((view))))));
9725
9726 if (caja_directory_are_all_files_seen (view->details->model)) {
9727 /* Unschedule a pending update and schedule a new one with the minimal
9728 * update interval. This gives the view a short chance at gathering the
9729 * (cached) deep counts.
9730 */
9731 unschedule_display_of_pending_files (view);
9732 schedule_timeout_display_of_pending_files (view, UPDATE_INTERVAL_MIN100);
9733 }
9734
9735 /* Start loading. */
9736
9737 /* Connect handlers to learn about loading progress. */
9738 view->details->done_loading_handler_id = g_signal_connectg_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("done_loading"
), (((GCallback) (done_loading_callback))), (view), ((void*)0
), (GConnectFlags) 0)
9739 (view->details->model, "done_loading",g_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("done_loading"
), (((GCallback) (done_loading_callback))), (view), ((void*)0
), (GConnectFlags) 0)
9740 G_CALLBACK (done_loading_callback), view)g_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("done_loading"
), (((GCallback) (done_loading_callback))), (view), ((void*)0
), (GConnectFlags) 0);
9741 view->details->load_error_handler_id = g_signal_connectg_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("load_error"
), (((GCallback) (load_error_callback))), (view), ((void*)0),
(GConnectFlags) 0)
9742 (view->details->model, "load_error",g_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("load_error"
), (((GCallback) (load_error_callback))), (view), ((void*)0),
(GConnectFlags) 0)
9743 G_CALLBACK (load_error_callback), view)g_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("load_error"
), (((GCallback) (load_error_callback))), (view), ((void*)0),
(GConnectFlags) 0);
9744
9745 /* Monitor the things needed to get the right icon. Also
9746 * monitor a directory's item count because the "size"
9747 * attribute is based on that, and the file's metadata
9748 * and possible custom name.
9749 */
9750 attributes =
9751 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTES_FOR_ICON(CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO | CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_LINK_INFO | CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_THUMBNAIL
) |
9752 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY_ITEM_COUNT |
9753 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO |
9754 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_LINK_INFO |
9755 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_MOUNT |
9756 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_EXTENSION_INFO;
9757
9758 caja_directory_file_monitor_add (view->details->model,
9759 &view->details->model,
9760 view->details->show_hidden_files,
9761 attributes,
9762 files_added_callback, view);
9763
9764 view->details->files_added_handler_id = g_signal_connectg_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("files_added"
), (((GCallback) (files_added_callback))), (view), ((void*)0)
, (GConnectFlags) 0)
9765 (view->details->model, "files_added",g_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("files_added"
), (((GCallback) (files_added_callback))), (view), ((void*)0)
, (GConnectFlags) 0)
9766 G_CALLBACK (files_added_callback), view)g_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("files_added"
), (((GCallback) (files_added_callback))), (view), ((void*)0)
, (GConnectFlags) 0);
9767 view->details->files_changed_handler_id = g_signal_connectg_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("files_changed"
), (((GCallback) (files_changed_callback))), (view), ((void*)
0), (GConnectFlags) 0)
9768 (view->details->model, "files_changed",g_signal_connect_data ((view->details->model), ("files_changed"

9900static void
9901disconnect_model_handlers (FMDirectoryView *view)
9902{
9903 if (view->details->model == NULL((void*)0)) {
9904 return;
9905 }
9906 disconnect_directory_handler (view, &view->details->files_added_handler_id);
9907 disconnect_directory_handler (view, &view->details->files_changed_handler_id);
9908 disconnect_directory_handler (view, &view->details->done_loading_handler_id);
9909 disconnect_directory_handler (view, &view->details->load_error_handler_id);
9910 disconnect_directory_as_file_handler (view, &view->details->file_changed_handler_id);
9911 caja_file_cancel_call_when_ready (view->details->directory_as_file,
9912 metadata_for_directory_as_file_ready_callback,
9913 view);
9914 caja_directory_cancel_callback (view->details->model,
9915 metadata_for_files_in_directory_ready_callback,
9916 view);
9917 caja_directory_file_monitor_remove (view->details->model,
9918 &view->details->model);

9920 &view->details->directory_as_file);

10100static gboolean
10101real_is_read_only (FMDirectoryView *view)
10102{
10103 CajaFile *file;
10104
10105 if (!fm_directory_view_is_editable (view)) {
10106 return TRUE(!(0));
10107 }
10108
10109 file = fm_directory_view_get_directory_as_file (view);
10110 if (file != NULL((void*)0)) {
10111 return !caja_file_can_write (file);
10112 }
10113 return FALSE(0);
10114}

10423static void
10424revert_slashes (char *string)
10425{

10498typedef struct {
10499 FMDirectoryView *view;

10507
10508static void
10509handle_netscape_url_drop_ask_cb (GObject *source_object,
10510 GAsyncResult *res,
10511 gpointer user_data)
10512{
10513 NetscapeUrlDropAsk *data;
10514 GdkDragAction action;
10515 GFileInfo *info;
10516 GFile *f;
10517 const char *mime_type;
10518
10519 data = user_data;
10520 f = G_FILE (source_object)((((GFile*) (void *) ((source_object)))));
10521
10522 info = g_file_query_info_finish (f, res, NULL((void*)0));
10523 mime_type = NULL((void*)0);
10524
10525 if (info) {
10526 mime_type = g_file_info_get_content_type (info);
10527 }
10528
10529 if (mime_type != NULL((void*)0) &&
10530 (g_content_type_equals (mime_type, "text/html") ||
10531 g_content_type_equals (mime_type, "text/xml") ||
10532 g_content_type_equals (mime_type, "application/xhtml+xml"))) {
10533 action = GDK_ACTION_LINK;
10534 } else if (mime_type != NULL((void*)0) &&
10535 g_content_type_equals (mime_type, "text/plain")) {
10536 action = ask_link_action (data->view);
10537 } else {
10538 action = GDK_ACTION_COPY;
10539 }
10540 if (info) {
10541 g_object_unref (info);
10542 }
10543
10544 if (action != 0) {
10545 fm_directory_view_handle_netscape_url_drop (data->view,
10546 data->encoded_url,
10547 data->target_uri,
10548 action,
10549 data->x, data->y);
10550 }
10551
10552 g_object_unref (data->view);
10553 g_object_unref (data->cancellable);
10554 if (data->timeout != 0) {
10555 g_source_remove (data->timeout);
10556 }
10557 g_free (data->encoded_url);
10558 g_free (data->target_uri);
10559 g_free (data);
10560}
10561
10562static gboolean
10563handle_netscape_url_drop_timeout (gpointer user_data)
10564{
10565 NetscapeUrlDropAsk *data;
10566
10567 data = user_data;
10568
10569 g_cancellable_cancel (data->cancellable);
10570 data->timeout = 0;
10571
10572 return FALSE(0);
10573}

10597void
10598fm_directory_view_handle_netscape_url_drop (FMDirectoryView *view,
10599 const char *encoded_url,
10600 const char *target_uri,
10601 GdkDragAction action,
10602 int x,
10603 int y)
10604{
10605 GdkPoint point;
10606 char *url, *title;
10607 char *container_uri;
10608 char **bits;
10609 GList *uri_list = NULL((void*)0);
10610 GFile *f;
10611
10612 if (encoded_url == NULL((void*)0)) {
10613 return;
10614 }
10615
10616 container_uri = NULL((void*)0);
10617 if (target_uri == NULL((void*)0)) {
10618 container_uri = fm_directory_view_get_backing_uri (view);
10619 g_assert (container_uri != NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_336
; if (container_uri != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_336 = 1; else
_g_boolean_var_336 = 0; _g_boolean_var_336; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c", 10619, ((const char*) (
__func__)), "container_uri != NULL"); } while (0);
10620 }
10621
10622 f = g_file_new_for_uri (target_uri != NULL((void*)0) ? target_uri : container_uri);
10623 if (!g_file_is_native (f)) {
10624 eel_show_warning_dialog (_("Drag and drop is not supported.")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Drag and drop is not supported.", 5),
10625 _("Drag and drop is only supported on local file systems.")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Drag and drop is only supported on local file systems."
, 5),
10626 fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view));
10627 g_object_unref (f);
10628 g_free (container_uri);
10629 return;
10630 }
10631 g_object_unref (f);
10632
10633 /* _NETSCAPE_URL_ works like this: $URL\n$TITLE */
10634 bits = g_strsplit (encoded_url, "\n", 0);
10635 switch (g_strv_length (bits)) {
10636 case 0:
10637 g_strfreev (bits);
10638 g_free (container_uri);
10639 return;
10640 case 1:
10641 url = bits[0];
10642 title = NULL((void*)0);
10643 break;
10644 default:
10645 url = bits[0];
10646 title = bits[1];
10647 }
10648
10649 if (action == GDK_ACTION_ASK) {
10650 NetscapeUrlDropAsk *data;
10651
10652 f = g_file_new_for_uri (url);
10653 data = g_new0 (NetscapeUrlDropAsk, 1)(NetscapeUrlDropAsk *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (
1); gsize __s = sizeof (NetscapeUrlDropAsk); gpointer __p; if
(__s == 1) __p = g_malloc0 (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p
(__n) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L
*2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc0 (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc0_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
10654 data->view = g_object_ref (view)((__typeof__ (view)) (g_object_ref) (view));
10655 data->cancellable = g_cancellable_new ();
10656 data->encoded_url = g_strdup (encoded_url)g_strdup_inline (encoded_url);
10657 data->target_uri = g_strdup (target_uri)g_strdup_inline (target_uri);
10658 data->x = x;
10659 data->y = y;
10660 /* Ensure we wait at most 1 second for mimetype */
10661 data->timeout = g_timeout_add (1000,
10662 handle_netscape_url_drop_timeout,
10663 data);
10664 g_file_query_info_async (f,
10665 G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_STANDARD_CONTENT_TYPE"standard::content-type", 0,
10666 0, data->cancellable,
10667 handle_netscape_url_drop_ask_cb,
10668 data);
10669
10670 g_strfreev (bits);
10671 g_free (container_uri);
10672 return;
10673 }
10674
10675 fm_directory_view_widget_to_file_operation_position_xy (view, &x, &y);
10676
10677 /* We don't support GDK_ACTION_ASK or GDK_ACTION_PRIVATE
10678 * and we don't support combinations either. */
10679 if ((action != GDK_ACTION_DEFAULT) &&
10680 (action != GDK_ACTION_COPY) &&
10681 (action != GDK_ACTION_MOVE) &&
10682 (action != GDK_ACTION_LINK)) {
10683 eel_show_warning_dialog (_("Drag and drop is not supported.")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Drag and drop is not supported.", 5),
10684 _("An invalid drag type was used.")dcgettext (((void*)0), "An invalid drag type was used.", 5),
10685 fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view));
10686 g_strfreev (bits);
10687 g_free (container_uri);
10688 return;
10689 }
10690
10691 if (action == GDK_ACTION_LINK) {
10692 char *link_name;
10693
10694 if (eel_str_is_empty (title)) {
10695 GFile *f;
10696
10697 f = g_file_new_for_uri (url);
10698 link_name = g_file_get_basename (f);
10699 g_object_unref (f);
10700 } else {
10701 link_name = g_strdup (title)g_strdup_inline (title);
10702 }
10703
10704 if (!eel_str_is_empty (link_name)) {
10705 GdkScreen *screen;
10706 int screen_num;
10707 char *link_display_name;
10708 GError *error = NULL((void*)0);
10709 gboolean success;
10710
10711 link_display_name = g_strdup_printf (_("Link to %s")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Link to %s", 5), link_name);
10712
10713 /* The filename can't contain slashes, strip em.
10714 (the basename of http://foo/ is http://foo/) */
10715 revert_slashes (link_name);
10716
10717 point.x = x;
10718 point.y = y;
10719
10720 screen = gtk_widget_get_screen (GTK_WIDGET (view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((view))))));
10721 screen_num = gdk_x11_screen_get_screen_number (screen);
10722
10723 success = caja_link_local_create (target_uri != NULL((void*)0) ? target_uri : container_uri,
10724 link_name,
10725 link_display_name,
10726 "mate-fs-bookmark",
10727 url,
10728 &point,
10729 screen_num,
10730 TRUE(!(0)),
10731 &error);
10732 if (!success) {
10733 if (error) {
10734 eel_show_error_dialog (_("Link Creation Failed")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Link Creation Failed", 5),
10735 error->message, NULL((void*)0));
10736 g_error_free (error);
10737 } else {
10738 gchar *error_message = g_strdup_printf (_("Cannot create the link to %s")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Cannot create the link to %s", 5), url);
10739 eel_show_error_dialog (_("Link Creation Failed")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Link Creation Failed", 5),
10740 error_message, NULL((void*)0));
10741 g_free (error_message);
10742 }
10743 }
10744
10745 g_free (link_display_name);
10746 }
10747 g_free (link_name);
10748 } else {
10749 GArray *points;
10750
10751 GdkPoint tmp_point = { 0, 0 };
10752
10753 /* pass in a 1-item array of icon positions, relative to x, y */
10754 points = g_array_new (FALSE(0), TRUE(!(0)), sizeof (GdkPoint));
10755 g_array_append_val (points, tmp_point)g_array_append_vals (points, &(tmp_point), 1);
10756
10757 uri_list = g_list_append (uri_list, url);
10758
10759 fm_directory_view_move_copy_items (uri_list, points,
10760 target_uri != NULL((void*)0) ? target_uri : container_uri,
10761 action, x, y, view);
10762
10763 g_list_free (uri_list);
10764 g_array_free (points, TRUE(!(0)));
10765 }
10766
10767 g_strfreev (bits);
10768 g_free (container_uri);
10769}

10771void
10772fm_directory_view_handle_uri_list_drop (FMDirectoryView *view,
10773 const char *item_uris,
10774 const char *target_uri,
10775 GdkDragAction action,
10776 int x,
10777 int y)
10778{
10779 gchar **uri_list;
10780 GList *real_uri_list = NULL((void*)0);
10781 char *container_uri;
10782 int n_uris, i;
10783 GArray *points;
10784
10785 if (item_uris == NULL((void*)0)) {
10786 return;
10787 }
10788
10789 container_uri = NULL((void*)0);
10790 if (target_uri == NULL((void*)0)) {
10791 container_uri = fm_directory_view_get_backing_uri (view);
10792 g_assert (container_uri != NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_337
; if (container_uri != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_337 = 1; else
_g_boolean_var_337 = 0; _g_boolean_var_337; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c", 10792, ((const char*) (
__func__)), "container_uri != NULL"); } while (0);
10793 }
10794
10795 if (action == GDK_ACTION_ASK) {
10796 action = caja_drag_drop_action_ask
10797 (GTK_WIDGET (view)((((GtkWidget*) (void *) ((view))))),
10798 GDK_ACTION_MOVE | GDK_ACTION_COPY | GDK_ACTION_LINK);
10799 if (action == 0) {
10800 g_free (container_uri);
10801 return;
10802 }
10803 }
10804
10805 /* We don't support GDK_ACTION_ASK or GDK_ACTION_PRIVATE
10806 * and we don't support combinations either. */
10807 if ((action != GDK_ACTION_DEFAULT) &&
10808 (action != GDK_ACTION_COPY) &&
10809 (action != GDK_ACTION_MOVE) &&
10810 (action != GDK_ACTION_LINK)) {
10811 eel_show_warning_dialog (_("Drag and drop is not supported.")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Drag and drop is not supported.", 5),
10812 _("An invalid drag type was used.")dcgettext (((void*)0), "An invalid drag type was used.", 5),
10813 fm_directory_view_get_containing_window (view));
10814 g_free (container_uri);
10815 return;
10816 }
10817
10818 n_uris = 0;
10819 uri_list = g_uri_list_extract_uris (item_uris);
10820 for (i = 0; uri_list[i] != NULL((void*)0); i++) {
10821 real_uri_list = g_list_append (real_uri_list, uri_list[i]);
10822 n_uris++;
10823 }
10824 g_free (uri_list);
10825
10826 /* do nothing if no real uris are left */
10827 if (n_uris == 0) {
10828 g_free (container_uri);
10829 return;
10830 }
10831
10832 if (n_uris == 1) {
10833 GdkPoint tmp_point = { 0, 0 };
10834
10835 /* pass in a 1-item array of icon positions, relative to x, y */
10836 points = g_array_new (FALSE(0), TRUE(!(0)), sizeof (GdkPoint));
10837 g_array_append_val (points, tmp_point)g_array_append_vals (points, &(tmp_point), 1);
10838 } else {
10839 points = NULL((void*)0);
10840 }
10841
10842 fm_directory_view_widget_to_file_operation_position_xy (view, &x, &y);
10843
10844 fm_directory_view_move_copy_items (real_uri_list, points,
10845 target_uri != NULL((void*)0) ? target_uri : container_uri,
10846 action, x, y, view);
10847
10848 g_list_free_full (real_uri_list, g_free);
10849
10850 if (points != NULL((void*)0))
10851 g_array_free (points, TRUE(!(0)));
10852
10853 g_free (container_uri);
10854}

10924 filename = NULL((void*)0);
10925 if (direct_save_uri != NULL((void*)0)) {
10926 GFile *direct_save_full;
10927
10928 direct_save_full = g_file_new_for_uri (direct_save_uri);
10929 filename = g_file_get_basename (direct_save_full);
10930 }
10931 if (filename == NULL((void*)0)) {
10932 /* Translators: This is the filename used for when you dnd raw
10933 * data to a directory, if the source didn't supply a name.
10934 */
10935 filename = _("dropped data")dcgettext (((void*)0), "dropped data", 5);
10936 }
10937
10938 fm_directory_view_new_file_with_initial_contents (
10939 view, target_uri != NULL((void*)0) ? target_uri : container_uri,
10940 filename, raw_data, length, &pos);
10941
10942 g_free (container_uri);
10943}

10959static void

, 10973, ((const char*) (__func__)), "directory_view->details->slot == NULL"
); } while (0);

))))));

10979 directory_view->details->window = window;

10990 directory_view, 0);

10992
10993 g_signal_connect_object (directory_view->details->window,
10994 "backup-files-mode-changed", G_CALLBACK (backup_files_mode_changed)((GCallback) (backup_files_mode_changed)),
10995 directory_view, 0);
10996 fm_directory_view_init_show_backup_files (directory_view);
10997
10998 break;
10999 default:
11000 G_OBJECT_WARN_INVALID_PROPERTY_ID (object, prop_id, pspec)do { GObject *_glib__object = (GObject*) ((object)); GParamSpec
*_glib__pspec = (GParamSpec*) ((pspec)); guint _glib__property_id
= ((prop_id)); g_warning ("%s:%d: invalid %s id %u for \"%s\" of type '%s' in '%s'"
, "fm-directory-view.c", 11000, ("property"), _glib__property_id
, _glib__pspec->name, g_type_name ((((((GTypeClass*) (((GTypeInstance
*) (_glib__pspec))->g_class))->g_type)))), (g_type_name
((((((GTypeClass*) (((GTypeInstance*) (_glib__object))->g_class
))->g_type)))))); } while (0);

11002 }

11004
11005gboolean
11006fm_directory_view_handle_scroll_event (FMDirectoryView *directory_view,
11007 GdkEventScroll *event)
11008{
11009 static gdouble total_delta_y = 0;
11010 gdouble delta_x, delta_y;
11011
11012 if (event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK) {
11013 switch (event->direction) {
11014 case GDK_SCROLL_UP:
11015 /* Zoom In */
11016 fm_directory_view_bump_zoom_level (directory_view, 1);
11017 return TRUE(!(0));
11018
11019 case GDK_SCROLL_DOWN:
11020 /* Zoom Out */
11021 fm_directory_view_bump_zoom_level (directory_view, -1);
11022 return TRUE(!(0));
11023
11024 case GDK_SCROLL_SMOOTH:
11025 gdk_event_get_scroll_deltas ((const GdkEvent *) event,
11026 &delta_x, &delta_y);
11027
11028 /* try to emulate a normal scrolling event by summing deltas */
11029 total_delta_y += delta_y;
11030
11031 if (total_delta_y >= 1) {
11032 total_delta_y = 0;
11033 /* emulate scroll down */
11034 fm_directory_view_bump_zoom_level (directory_view, -1);
11035 return TRUE(!(0));
11036 } else if (total_delta_y <= - 1) {
11037 total_delta_y = 0;
11038 /* emulate scroll up */
11039 fm_directory_view_bump_zoom_level (directory_view, 1);
11040 return TRUE(!(0));
11041 } else {
11042 /* eat event */
11043 return TRUE(!(0));
11044 }
11045
11046 case GDK_SCROLL_LEFT:
11047 case GDK_SCROLL_RIGHT:
11048 break;
11049
11050 default:
11051 g_assert_not_reached ()do { g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c"
, 11051, ((const char*) (__func__)), ((void*)0)); } while (0);
11052 }
11053 }
11054
11055 return FALSE(0);
11056}
11057
11058/* handle Shift+Scroll, which will cause a zoom-in/out */
11059static gboolean
11060fm_directory_view_scroll_event (GtkWidget *widget,
11061 GdkEventScroll *event)
11062{
11063 FMDirectoryView *directory_view;
11064
11065 directory_view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (widget)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((widget)))));
11066 if (fm_directory_view_handle_scroll_event (directory_view, event)) {
11067 return TRUE(!(0));
11068 }
11069
11070 return GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (parent_class)((((GtkWidgetClass*) (void *) ((parent_class)))))->scroll_event (widget, event);
11071}
11072
11073static void
11074fm_directory_view_parent_set (GtkWidget *widget,
11075 GtkWidget *old_parent)
11076{
11077 FMDirectoryView *view;
11078 GtkWidget *parent;
11079
11080 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (widget)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((widget)))));
11081
11082 parent = gtk_widget_get_parent (widget);
11083 g_assert (parent == NULL || old_parent == NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_344
; if (parent == ((void*)0) || old_parent == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_344
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_344 = 0; _g_boolean_var_344; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c"
, 11083, ((const char*) (__func__)), "parent == NULL || old_parent == NULL"
); } while (0);
11084
11085 if (GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (parent_class)((((GtkWidgetClass*) (void *) ((parent_class)))))->parent_set != NULL((void*)0)) {
11086 GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (parent_class)((((GtkWidgetClass*) (void *) ((parent_class)))))->parent_set (widget, old_parent);
11087 }
11088
11089 if (parent != NULL((void*)0)) {
11090 g_assert (old_parent == NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_345
; if (old_parent == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_345 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_345
= 0; _g_boolean_var_345; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "fm-directory-view.c", 11090, ((const char*) (
__func__)), "old_parent == NULL"); } while (0);
11091
11092 if (view->details->slot ==
11093 caja_window_info_get_active_slot (view->details->window)) {
11094 view->details->active = TRUE(!(0));
11095
11096 fm_directory_view_merge_menus (view);
11097 schedule_update_menus (view);
11098 }
11099 } else {
11100 fm_directory_view_unmerge_menus (view);
11101 remove_update_menus_timeout_callback (view);
11102 }
11103}

11286
11287static void
11288undo_redo_menu_update_callback (CajaUndoStackManager* manager, gpointer arg, gpointer data)
11289{
11290 FMDirectoryView *view;
11291 view = FM_DIRECTORY_VIEW (data)((((FMDirectoryView*) (void *) ((data)))));
11292
11293 CajaUndoStackMenuData* menudata = (CajaUndoStackMenuData*) arg;
11294
11295 g_free(view->details->undo_action_label);
11296 g_free(view->details->undo_action_description);
11297 g_free(view->details->redo_action_label);
11298 g_free(view->details->redo_action_description);
11299
11300 view->details->undo_active = menudata->undo_label ? TRUE(!(0)) : FALSE(0);
11301 view->details->redo_active = menudata->redo_label ? TRUE(!(0)) : FALSE(0);
11302
11303 view->details->undo_action_label = g_strdup (menudata->undo_label)g_strdup_inline (menudata->undo_label);
11304 view->details->undo_action_description = g_strdup (menudata->undo_description)g_strdup_inline (menudata->undo_description);
11305 view->details->redo_action_label = g_strdup (menudata->redo_label)g_strdup_inline (menudata->redo_label);
11306 view->details->redo_action_description = g_strdup (menudata->redo_description)g_strdup_inline (menudata->redo_description);
11307
11308 schedule_update_menus (view);
11309}
